WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.870 --> 00:00:05.382
I told you to sit down because
today's topic will be a bit longer.

00:00:07.046 --> 00:00:09.947
Keep in mind that I have been
working on this for five months

00:00:10.139 --> 00:00:12.567
I believe it is very important
to pass it on to you.

00:00:12.592 --> 00:00:14.583
I managed to summarize.

00:00:15.035 --> 00:00:21.393
Most of these observations
and revelations came from traveling

00:00:21.426 --> 00:00:24.057
throughout Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina

00:00:24.317 --> 00:00:32.290
working with many young people, and through
long prayer and theological examination.

00:00:32.316 --> 00:00:37.859
I want to share them with
you. Since these are very sensitive topics

00:00:38.201 --> 00:00:41.748
You know usually when
 a topic is very sensitive

00:00:41.984 --> 00:00:46.990
the common folk say: 'Let's
not stir the pot', let it remain calm.

00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:51.028
However, precisely in those sensitive
areas, the pearl is often hidden."

00:00:51.996 --> 00:00:55.268
I remember when I was talking
about this topic at the men's formation

00:00:55.479 --> 00:00:59.592
I mentioned the Grimm brothers'
fairy tale about Iron John.

00:00:59.625 --> 00:01:02.914
Are you familiar with that tale?

00:01:04.654 --> 00:01:09.148
As Tolkien was often in God's spirit,
I believe the Grimm brothers were also.

00:01:09.696 --> 00:01:12.948
Anyway, I'll shorten it to the maximum.

00:01:13.939 --> 00:01:17.740
It's about an enchanted lake in the forest.

00:01:17.787 --> 00:01:20.083
There was an enchanted lake in the forest,

00:01:20.194 --> 00:01:24.628
and many people who went
into that forest would disappear.

00:01:25.221 --> 00:01:29.099
Then, one young man had a good
 idea and went there with his dog.

00:01:29.525 --> 00:01:32.905
He watched where the dog went,
and the dog was the first to perish.

00:01:32.946 --> 00:01:38.862
Then, he informed the king exactly where that
enchanted lake with living mud was located.

00:01:38.927 --> 00:01:42.761
Inside, they found a monster
 they called the Wild Man

00:01:43.348 --> 00:01:47.558
They imprisoned him in the
royal palace and he was exposed.

00:01:48.809 --> 00:01:54.898
And now, the king's son, the prince,
was playing with a golden ball

00:01:55.050 --> 00:01:58.787
which is a common motif in fairy tales.
In fact, it is taken from the Bible.

00:01:58.901 --> 00:02:03.582
We see that even in
"The Lord of the Rings," there is that ring

00:02:05.497 --> 00:02:09.112
for which people were willing
to risk everything. A very common motif.

00:02:09.482 --> 00:02:16.362
Actually, this motif emerges from the Gospel
when Jesus speaks about the precious pearl

00:02:16.466 --> 00:02:20.348
that a person, once he finds it, is
willing to sell everything for that pearl.

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:23.702
Sell everything and buy that field
where he found that pearl.

00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:29.446
This represents something
precious in our life, in our soul

00:02:29.868 --> 00:02:34.176
something for which we are sure is
the purpose of our existence, God's will.

00:02:34.588 --> 00:02:40.795
All people who have indeed known God
and achieved holiness in life here on Earth

00:02:41.078 --> 00:02:44.299
no matter how difficult it was for them,
no matter how persecuted they were

00:02:44.386 --> 00:02:49.101
like Padre Pio, and when they told him
to share those struggles with someone

00:02:49.268 --> 00:02:52.732
he said: "I won't, I don't want to
give anyone the sweetest part."

00:02:54.366 --> 00:02:58.683
So, this boy was playing
with the golden ball

00:02:58.890 --> 00:03:03.279
and it fell out of the window and
ended up in the wild man's cage.

00:03:04.362 --> 00:03:08.798
What was significant then,
especially as it was a male formation,

00:03:08.822 --> 00:03:12.365
was that the key to that cage
was under his mother's pillow.

00:03:13.103 --> 00:03:14.621
And that is very interesting.

00:03:14.646 --> 00:03:20.980
We know that as young men, as the
Holy Scriptures say, we should learn to

00:03:21.028 --> 00:03:24.804
separate ourselves from our parents, from
our mother in order to cling to our wife.

00:03:25.502 --> 00:03:31.320
So, he had to somehow take
the key that was under his mother's pillow.

00:03:31.391 --> 00:03:33.716
The symbolism is much deeper.

00:03:34.087 --> 00:03:35.555
It's not just about that

00:03:35.857 --> 00:03:40.548
it's about the fact that
there are certain family secrets

00:03:40.737 --> 00:03:44.699
certain family matters, and sins
that must not be talked about.

00:03:45.072 --> 00:03:47.259
How much it burdened our people.

00:03:47.489 --> 00:03:52.213
From what I've heard in many family stories,
Bleiburg couldn't be mentioned for fifty years.

00:03:52.545 --> 00:03:56.229
Your grandfather died, your
uncle died, that's not talked about.

00:03:56.344 --> 00:03:59.078
You must not talk about it.
The conversation starts about the war

00:03:59.395 --> 00:04:01.150
I've been in that family's home

00:04:01.210 --> 00:04:04.814
Father has PTSD, so the son knows
something's not right with his father

00:04:04.904 --> 00:04:08.045
the story begins, no! silence!
it's not talked about.

00:04:08.670 --> 00:04:11.700
That's how we keep locked-up memories

00:04:12.779 --> 00:04:14.446
and we never get to the pearl.

00:04:15.156 --> 00:04:17.843
But this guy gathered his courage

00:04:17.868 --> 00:04:20.770
took the key that was
under his mother's pillow

00:04:21.063 --> 00:04:24.943
and unlocked the cage of the wild man.

00:04:25.445 --> 00:04:27.590
The wild man didn't attack him.

00:04:27.833 --> 00:04:33.715
Grimm describes the eight
stages of his maturation there.

00:04:34.095 --> 00:04:39.082
Through those stages, he learned to
deal with the wild man in himself.

00:04:39.568 --> 00:04:42.909
That's what we need to do.

00:04:43.106 --> 00:04:46.980
We need to learn to deal with
those wild things that are locked

00:04:47.005 --> 00:04:50.940
that are suppressed
because that's where our pearl is.

00:04:51.224 --> 00:04:53.125
What's very important.

00:04:53.181 --> 00:04:56.707
This is actually a combination of the
parable of the hidden pearl

00:04:56.738 --> 00:05:00.846
and of the strong man who
holds his family, his house tied.

00:05:01.134 --> 00:05:04.059
When Jesus speaks
about deliverance in exorcisms

00:05:04.146 --> 00:05:07.484
He uses precisely that parable
(Luke 11:21-22)

00:05:08.032 --> 00:05:13.084
"When a strong man, fully armed, guards
his own house, his possessions are safe."

00:05:13.424 --> 00:05:17.159
"But when someone stronger attacks
and overpowers him, that is Christ

00:05:17.242 --> 00:05:20.960
he takes away the armor in which the
man trusted and divides up the spoils."

00:05:21.397 --> 00:05:23.401
In Matthew 12, 29

00:05:23.583 --> 00:05:27.347
"Or else how can one enter into
a strong man's house, and spoil his goods

00:05:27.656 --> 00:05:31.605
except he first bind the strong
man? Then he will spoil his house."

00:05:32.414 --> 00:05:38.419
We will have to enter into that struggle,
into wrestling with that wild man.

00:05:38.499 --> 00:05:40.715
Why? To get to that pearl.

00:05:41.105 --> 00:05:44.344
I've met many believers who don't live

00:05:44.368 --> 00:05:48.664
even near the fulfillment and
the plan that God had for them

00:05:48.851 --> 00:05:53.828
precisely because they lack the courage
to engage in a battle with themselves

00:05:54.296 --> 00:05:59.468
to deal with those monsters from the closet,
their family history, their personal history

00:05:59.784 --> 00:06:06.666
and to allow Christ, the stronger
man, to enter and bind the strong man.

00:06:08.071 --> 00:06:12.708
So that doesn't happen to us,
we'll go through five very tricky points

00:06:13.199 --> 00:06:16.148
precisely to find direction for the future

00:06:16.553 --> 00:06:20.850
because I believe these topics will be
very important. They are important today

00:06:21.176 --> 00:06:23.449
and they will be very
important in the future.

00:06:23.767 --> 00:06:28.428
It is the relationship between faith and
nationalism, that is, faith and patriotism.

00:06:29.609 --> 00:06:35.348
We see that many troubles, wars, and conflicts
have happened precisely because of this

00:06:36.007 --> 00:06:39.735
and there were few
formed believers who knew

00:06:39.759 --> 00:06:46.033
when some ideology or war threatened
to take and choose the right standpoint

00:06:46.174 --> 00:06:48.277
small number, a very small number.

00:06:48.595 --> 00:06:52.348
That's where the curse fell
on our people and our families.

00:06:52.578 --> 00:06:54.614
Find where that healthy boundary is

00:06:54.888 --> 00:06:59.622
What the difference is between patriotism
or love of country and nationalism.

00:07:00.073 --> 00:07:02.450
That will be very important for us.

00:07:03.038 --> 00:07:07.228
The second is nurturing family and
national memory. What I just mentioned.

00:07:07.840 --> 00:07:10.228
Since it's often difficult and burdensome

00:07:10.386 --> 00:07:16.068
we decide not to enter that space, yet
that is precisely where many solutions lie.

00:07:16.878 --> 00:07:20.428
Third, when we discover what it is about

00:07:20.908 --> 00:07:24.317
the prayer for the ancestors. There is so
much controversy about that in the church.

00:07:24.603 --> 00:07:28.068
It's interesting to note that many
individuals who did not directly encounter

00:07:28.092 --> 00:07:31.903
human plight and suffering
have unique "smart" perspectives.

00:07:32.816 --> 00:07:36.618
That's why we want to hear what the catechism
tells us, what the Church's experience tells us

00:07:36.642 --> 00:07:38.951
and how we actually
pray for the deceased.

00:07:39.388 --> 00:07:41.868
The terminology we
use is also very important.

00:07:41.892 --> 00:07:45.036
We will learn not to fall into those
traps again and avoid extremes.

00:07:46.425 --> 00:07:47.301
Fourth

00:07:47.999 --> 00:07:52.700
very important for our time,
 are there chosen nations today?

00:07:52.962 --> 00:07:56.032
The heresy that often
exists about messianic nations.

00:07:57.831 --> 00:07:59.628
So many times has that misled people.

00:08:00.517 --> 00:08:04.388
And yet, we see that God uses
 some nations in a particular way

00:08:04.665 --> 00:08:08.462
It is also very important to find a healthy
balance there. These are very tricky areas.

00:08:09.183 --> 00:08:10.804
Fifth.

00:08:11.415 --> 00:08:13.388
The question of our diaspora.

00:08:13.855 --> 00:08:20.428
Is God calling them to be light where
they are, or is He calling them to return?

00:08:20.547 --> 00:08:27.028
We will see that the return has a very, very
deep biblical and theological dimension.

00:08:27.460 --> 00:08:31.108
Those are the five points
we will deal with today. Why?

00:08:31.647 --> 00:08:36.068
Pope Francis has given
a great diagnosis of today's society.

00:08:37.289 --> 00:08:40.508
We have a problem,
and the Pope offers a cure.

00:08:40.961 --> 00:08:44.348
The Pope calls
today's society an uprooted society.

00:08:45.220 --> 00:08:48.457
In his book
"God is Young," the Pope says this:

00:08:51.619 --> 00:08:52.908
The journalist asks him

00:08:53.042 --> 00:08:57.891
since the Pope has diagnosed the problem of
today's world, especially of young people

00:08:58.217 --> 00:09:00.286
is uprootedness, an uprooted society.

00:09:00.808 --> 00:09:02.377
The Pope gives this diagnosis.

00:09:02.528 --> 00:09:04.978
By an uprooted society, I mean a society

00:09:05.168 --> 00:09:10.059
made up of people and families who are
losing little by little their connections

00:09:10.377 --> 00:09:15.228
that life tissue so important
for us  to feel part of each other

00:09:15.751 --> 00:09:22.308
to feel with others as participants in a
joint endeavor and common in a broader sense.

00:09:22.934 --> 00:09:26.148
Society is rooted if it belongs to history

00:09:26.710 --> 00:09:29.508
then it belongs to others in
the best sense of the word.

00:09:29.532 --> 00:09:34.448
On the contrary, it is uprooted if young
people grow up in families without history

00:09:34.860 --> 00:09:36.993
without memory, and thus without roots.

00:09:37.458 --> 00:09:40.387
Since childhood,
we all know how important roots are.

00:09:40.672 --> 00:09:45.372
Precisely physically, if there
are no roots, every wind throws us around.

00:09:45.943 --> 00:09:50.868
That's why, as parents and family, as
shepherds, we should primarily think about

00:09:50.892 --> 00:09:55.731
the areas where we will root ourselves,
create connections, and develop a life network

00:09:55.970 --> 00:09:59.482
that will enable us to feel at home.

00:10:00.339 --> 00:10:03.544
Alienation is terrible for a person,
the sense of not having roots

00:10:03.568 --> 00:10:05.268
of not belonging to anyone.

00:10:05.584 --> 00:10:08.547
There's nothing worse than
feeling like a stranger at home

00:10:08.572 --> 00:10:11.618
without the principle of equality
that you would share with other people.

00:10:11.649 --> 00:10:14.948
Our roots make us less
 alone and more complete.

00:10:20.042 --> 00:10:23.028
Individuals who are not
 aware of their own roots

00:10:24.122 --> 00:10:27.988
I know from my own experience, are
the most susceptible to manipulation.

00:10:28.780 --> 00:10:33.396
Jesus strength was in
knowing where he came from,

00:10:33.429 --> 00:10:35.544
where he was going,
and what his goal was.

00:10:35.776 --> 00:10:40.146
And when he argued with the Pharisees,
in the eighth chapter of John's Gospel

00:10:40.217 --> 00:10:42.717
He clearly provokes the
 Pharisees and tells them:

00:10:42.741 --> 00:10:46.569
"Yes, but I know where I came from
and where I am going, but you do not know."

00:10:48.731 --> 00:10:52.788
And this is a problem that I especially
encounter with young people today.

00:10:53.010 --> 00:10:55.892
The responsibility often lies with you,
the older ones.

00:10:56.368 --> 00:10:58.217
The Pope also emphasizes this.

00:10:58.455 --> 00:10:59.402
Let's do it like this:

00:10:59.426 --> 00:11:02.588
I'll ask only the young ones now,
and then I'll ask the older ones later.

00:11:03.531 --> 00:11:06.819
Who told you more?
I ask you, young people, first.

00:11:07.239 --> 00:11:13.151
About your roots, about your history,
about the place where you come from?

00:11:13.837 --> 00:11:16.268
Grandparents or fathers and mothers?

00:11:16.332 --> 00:11:19.621
Raise your hands if your
 grandparents told stories.

00:11:24.721 --> 00:11:27.760
Okay. And those whose
fathers and mothers told more stories?

00:11:29.012 --> 00:11:32.771
Great. Now, let's go back a little
before the time of indoctrination.

00:11:32.969 --> 00:11:36.115
Those of you who are a bit older

00:11:36.163 --> 00:11:39.639
Who told you more? Fathers
and mothers? You can raise your hands.

00:11:41.950 --> 00:11:44.868
No one. Ah, there are some.

00:11:45.439 --> 00:11:47.140
Grandparents?

00:11:48.958 --> 00:11:49.918
Many more.

00:11:50.702 --> 00:11:52.980
The Pope comes to the same conclusion,

00:11:53.004 --> 00:11:56.732
one of the solutions he offers is dialogue
between the older and the younger generation.

00:11:56.756 --> 00:11:59.527
Listen to this brilliant text
brought to us by Pope Francis.

00:12:00.067 --> 00:12:03.185
"I believe dialogue is a powerful
 way to save ourselves

00:12:03.209 --> 00:12:05.466
a dialogue between the young and the old.

00:12:05.521 --> 00:12:10.125
Interaction between the older and younger,
even temporarily skipping the adults.

00:12:10.831 --> 00:12:15.068
The young and the old need to talk,
and even more often. It's imperative.

00:12:15.479 --> 00:12:18.513
Both older and younger
generations should take the initiative.

00:12:18.546 --> 00:12:20.730
Passage in the Bible that goes like this:

00:12:20.792 --> 00:12:26.046
"Your old men shall dream dreams,
and your young men shall see visions."

00:12:26.789 --> 00:12:28.867
The new society rejects both.

00:12:29.114 --> 00:12:31.843
It rejects the young
 just as it rejects the old.

00:12:32.407 --> 00:12:38.428
Yet, for the old, salvation lies in
passing on memories to the young,

00:12:38.492 --> 00:12:40.949
which makes them
true dreamers of the future.

00:12:41.353 --> 00:12:45.997
On the other hand, salvation for the
young lies in receiving those teachings,

00:12:46.064 --> 00:12:49.759
those dreams and
continuing to live them in prophecy.

00:12:50.507 --> 00:12:57.259
For our young to see visions and be dreamers
themselves, to boldly face the future,

00:12:57.283 --> 00:13:00.560
it's necessary for them to listen to the
prophetic dreams of their ancestors.

00:13:00.900 --> 00:13:07.173
Old dreamers and young prophets—that is the
path of salvation for our uprooted society.

00:13:07.537 --> 00:13:10.581
Two generations of
derelicts can save everything.

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:14.948
The Pope gives the recipe:
old dreamers and young prophets.

00:13:20.879 --> 00:13:22.868
We see what the world is doing today.

00:13:22.892 --> 00:13:26.348
We have a remedy:
let the old go to nursing homes

00:13:27.986 --> 00:13:31.508
and let the young be raised
by the state and the media.

00:13:32.658 --> 00:13:38.835
But there is a great danger that if we
remain passive to what is happening

00:13:39.914 --> 00:13:43.436
we will lose touch with our roots

00:13:43.488 --> 00:13:47.679
and be blown away by the winds that are
blowing more and more strongly around us.

00:13:47.703 --> 00:13:49.726
There won't be any of us.

00:13:50.972 --> 00:13:53.365
My goal here is not to scare you,
but trust me, it's happening.

00:13:53.433 --> 00:13:57.708
It's already happening in our society today.
Will we remain passive?

00:13:58.658 --> 00:14:04.457
Will we allow the perversions our
grandparents never even imagined existed

00:14:04.482 --> 00:14:06.881
never even mentioned,

00:14:07.253 --> 00:14:10.360
to become part of our children's lives?

00:14:11.249 --> 00:14:14.772
That's why it's crucial
to raise young people

00:14:14.796 --> 00:14:18.388
who will know very well where
they came from and where they're going.

00:14:19.823 --> 00:14:21.107
Youth and history.

00:14:26.330 --> 00:14:30.147
When we talk about getting to know history

00:14:30.932 --> 00:14:36.588
we're not only talking about our family history
but specifically about national history as well.

00:14:37.059 --> 00:14:42.420
And here we come to the first tricky topic:
Relationship between belief and patriotism.

00:14:43.221 --> 00:14:45.582
(1. Faith and patriotism)
How many times has this been abused?

00:14:45.874 --> 00:14:52.563
So many times the nationalization of the church
or sacralization of the nation has happened.

00:14:53.222 --> 00:14:55.708
And it always had
catastrophic consequences.

00:14:56.358 --> 00:14:59.228
Yet, we must find that
healthy middle ground.

00:14:59.585 --> 00:15:03.371
That's why I've decided to walk
with you through the Holy Scriptures

00:15:03.457 --> 00:15:07.828
The Holy Scripture should always be
our guide in life. As the psalmist says:

00:15:08.090 --> 00:15:10.877
The word of God is a lamp to
my feet and alight to my path.

00:15:10.943 --> 00:15:15.188
Brothers and sisters, I am speaking to you
from my soul, from my heart, most sincerely

00:15:15.521 --> 00:15:19.484
When I was in the most complex
situations both in service and in life

00:15:20.055 --> 00:15:22.066
When I honestly came before God

00:15:22.331 --> 00:15:25.828
It never happened that the
Lord did not shed light on that situation

00:15:25.853 --> 00:15:30.157
and show me a solution through His word.
He was always, always faithful.

00:15:30.346 --> 00:15:34.428
Whenever that happened, God's word
enlightened me and showed me the way out.

00:15:35.243 --> 00:15:39.300
That's why we'll walk through the
Holy Scriptures and see where

00:15:39.339 --> 00:15:42.748
the roots of that healthy patriotism
we need to nurture lie.

00:15:43.319 --> 00:15:46.296
This is where I especially
appeal to you, young people.

00:15:46.367 --> 00:15:51.392
We must find a middle ground between two
extremes, both of which are demonological.

00:15:51.892 --> 00:15:55.787
Exorcists say that
extremes are always diabolical

00:15:55.835 --> 00:16:00.298
and that God's way is the middle
one, moderate but without mediocrity.

00:16:01.417 --> 00:16:05.179
These two extremes are radical nationalism

00:16:05.219 --> 00:16:09.871
Where we consider our people
to be superior, stronger, better

00:16:09.979 --> 00:16:13.714
and that gives us
justification to oppress others.

00:16:15.412 --> 00:16:20.830
The second extreme is more insidious and dangerous
because these attitudes can be easily recognized.

00:16:20.862 --> 00:16:26.988
We can immediately say who is like that
in Serbia, Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina.

00:16:27.583 --> 00:16:33.253
However, the more insidious one
is the attitude that no nation exists.

00:16:33.332 --> 00:16:36.988
That it doesn't matter at all, that we are
all one, especially if we are Christians.

00:16:38.020 --> 00:16:42.750
Why? Because it leads toward
the creation of a new world order

00:16:42.953 --> 00:16:47.782
in which there will be one nation,
one language, and one currency.

00:16:49.096 --> 00:16:52.301
Why? Because it's much,
much easier to manipulate.

00:16:52.769 --> 00:16:55.265
The kingdom of Antichrist
will be able to happen

00:16:55.289 --> 00:16:59.304
I'm talking about the Antichrist with a capital
"A", when these conditions are fulfilled.

00:16:59.772 --> 00:17:03.733
I don't care about conspiracy theories at all.
Whether it will be tomorrow or in 70-100 years

00:17:03.757 --> 00:17:06.832
I'm telling you what is written
in the Holy Scriptures about it.

00:17:07.092 --> 00:17:12.325
The Epistle of John, the Epistle to the
Thessalonians, as well as the Revelation.

00:17:12.965 --> 00:17:17.108
The Antichrist will bring a false
peace, and it will be on a global level.

00:17:17.467 --> 00:17:24.142
That's why there is a very strong movement that
wants to diminish and make the nation unimportant.

00:17:24.194 --> 00:17:28.574
This is perhaps best described
in that song by John Lennon.

00:17:28.691 --> 00:17:30.979
Imagine there's no heaven;
there are no countries.

00:17:31.109 --> 00:17:35.075
Nothing exists; we are all one,
and everything is so beautifully fluid.

00:17:35.789 --> 00:17:41.668
It is an uprooted society. I see that many
in the church have fallen into that trap.

00:17:41.977 --> 00:17:44.388
And now, how to find a healthy boundary?

00:17:44.689 --> 00:17:47.605
Let's go through the Holy Scriptures.
Right at the beginning

00:17:47.680 --> 00:17:53.188
In the Genesis 12: 1 God speaks to Abram,
 who wasn't yet called Abraham:

00:17:53.640 --> 00:17:59.748
"Go from your country, your people and your
father's household to the land I will show you."

00:18:00.081 --> 00:18:04.911
God wants to give Abram
a very specific land.

00:18:06.031 --> 00:18:09.237
Very specific.
Try touching this to any Jew.

00:18:10.014 --> 00:18:11.228
You won't fare well.

00:18:12.792 --> 00:18:17.508
And Abraham goes where God showed
him because He wants to give him that land.

00:18:18.533 --> 00:18:22.561
Genesis 12:7, Abraham comes to an oak tree

00:18:22.831 --> 00:18:27.984
There he builds an altar to the Lord
who appeared to him, and God speaks to him:

00:18:28.060 --> 00:18:30.748
"To your offspring, I will give this land."

00:18:32.153 --> 00:18:38.028
We see that the biblical
attitude is gratitude to God

00:18:38.052 --> 00:18:40.790
who gave us our specific homeland.

00:18:42.940 --> 00:18:48.195
Abraham was very careful about
where he would bury his ancestors.

00:18:48.839 --> 00:18:56.388
In Genesis 23, there is a discussion, a
trade one, between Abraham and Ephron.

00:18:56.610 --> 00:18:58.988
After his wife dies

00:18:59.012 --> 00:19:02.708
Abraham wants to buy a specific area
to be the burial place of the patriarchs.

00:19:03.176 --> 00:19:09.849
Unfortunately, today it's rarely visited
 because Hebron is quite a dangerous area.

00:19:09.873 --> 00:19:12.743
Both Muslims, Jews, and
Christians claim Abraham.

00:19:13.009 --> 00:19:17.108
It's always tense there, so guides avoid
going there. That's in today's Hebron.

00:19:17.742 --> 00:19:20.548
Genesis 23:17-20

00:19:20.825 --> 00:19:26.032
"So Ephron's field in Machpelah, near Mamre,
both the field and the cave in it and all the trees

00:19:26.056 --> 00:19:31.235
within the borders of the field-was deeded to Abraham
as his property in the presence of all the Hittites.

00:19:32.987 --> 00:19:39.145
So the field and the cave in it were deeded
to Abraham by the Hittites as a burial site."

00:19:39.556 --> 00:19:42.354
This became a holy place.
This is very relevant today

00:19:42.378 --> 00:19:47.060
because we are in the octave for All Saints
when we visit the graves of our ancestors.

00:19:47.449 --> 00:19:49.675
It's not just some mere tradition.

00:19:50.564 --> 00:19:55.460
Although we believe their souls are
not there, God has sanctified the graves.

00:19:55.814 --> 00:19:58.875
We see that Jacob, a patriarch

00:19:59.712 --> 00:20:05.136
when they found themselves in
exile due to famine in Egypt.

00:20:05.161 --> 00:20:07.268
Jacob was Abraham's grandson

00:20:07.966 --> 00:20:09.508
Abraham, Isaac, Jacob

00:20:10.302 --> 00:20:14.680
even though he was dying in
Egypt, requested to be buried there.

00:20:16.020 --> 00:20:18.588
Genesis 49:29-32. Then he
gave them these instructions:

00:20:18.778 --> 00:20:23.434
"I am about to be gathered to
my people. Bury me with my fathers

00:20:23.459 --> 00:20:30.897
in the cave in the field of Ephron the Hittite, the
cave in the field of Machpelah, near Mamre in Canaan

00:20:30.928 --> 00:20:35.661
which Abraham bought along with the field
as a burial place from Ephron the Hittite.

00:20:35.967 --> 00:20:41.744
There Abraham and Sarah were buried, there Isaac
and Rebekah were buried, and there I buried Leah.

00:20:42.049 --> 00:20:44.785
The field and the cave in it
were bought from the Hittites."

00:20:45.195 --> 00:20:48.989
And then there is an event which,
while I was considering the Bible

00:20:49.013 --> 00:20:52.628
strongly reminded me of
the funerals of "guest workers."

00:20:56.705 --> 00:21:01.348
Jacob died, and his sons, namely
Joseph, who was a governor of Pharaoh

00:21:01.458 --> 00:21:04.508
asked permission to go to another land

00:21:04.809 --> 00:21:08.268
from which they had left because
of famine and difficult conditions

00:21:09.010 --> 00:21:10.615
to bury his father, Jacob.

00:21:10.798 --> 00:21:13.286
And now it describes what
that procession looked like.

00:21:13.326 --> 00:21:16.948
Genesis 50: 7-8. 'So Joseph went up to bury his
father. All Pharaoh’s officials accompanied him

00:21:16.972 --> 00:21:20.485
the dignitaries of his court
and all the dignitaries of Egypt

00:21:20.510 --> 00:21:23.785
besides all the members of Joseph’s household and his
brothers and those belonging to his father’s household.

00:21:23.810 --> 00:21:28.469
Only their children and their flocks
and herds were left in Goshen. '

00:21:28.968 --> 00:21:36.108
And they went to Israel, which was
devastated by famine, and buried Jacob there.

00:21:37.100 --> 00:21:40.568
Doesn't that remind you
of those sad funeral scenes

00:21:40.593 --> 00:21:43.668
I used to see in the Bosanska
Posavina, in Herzegovina?

00:21:43.866 --> 00:21:47.220
The village, only five
grandmothers left, a grand funeral

00:21:47.244 --> 00:21:50.789
fifty German and Austrian
plates, the most expensive cars

00:21:50.813 --> 00:21:53.233
it's done, and then everyone goes back.

00:21:55.896 --> 00:21:58.508
Joseph, his son, requests the same.

00:21:58.881 --> 00:22:02.275
Although he was the first
associate of the Pharaoh

00:22:03.540 --> 00:22:05.692
and therefore he had
 to be buried in Egypt.

00:22:05.750 --> 00:22:08.778
Then he prophesies and
 on his deathbed says:

00:22:08.803 --> 00:22:09.318
Genesis 50:24-25

00:22:09.343 --> 00:22:12.913
Then Joseph said to his
brothers, “I am about to die.

00:22:12.938 --> 00:22:17.578
But God will surely come to your
aid and take you up out of this land

00:22:17.602 --> 00:22:21.908
to the land he promised on oath
to Abraham, Isaac and Jacob.”

00:22:21.932 --> 00:22:24.448
Joseph made the Israelites
swear an oath and said:

00:22:24.472 --> 00:22:29.120
“God will surely come to your aid, and then
you must carry my bones up from this place.”

00:22:29.144 --> 00:22:35.674
And this happened in the Book of Exodus
when the Israelites left after 400 years.

00:22:35.872 --> 00:22:38.664
We see it recorded in Exodus 13:19:

00:22:38.688 --> 00:22:44.354
Moses took the bones of Joseph with him because
Joseph had made the Israelites swear an oath.

00:22:44.378 --> 00:22:49.305
He had said: "God will surely come to your aid,
 and then you must carry my bones up with you."

00:22:49.511 --> 00:22:57.468
We see how strong an influence and
importance it had for the chosen people.

00:22:57.864 --> 00:23:02.061
Great graces often occur in
places where people's ancestors

00:23:02.085 --> 00:23:06.107
invoked the Name of God
without them knowing it.

00:23:07.290 --> 00:23:09.308
I personally experienced this.

00:23:09.333 --> 00:23:16.238
Through maturation and adolescence,
I was also a bit lost on this issue.

00:23:17.904 --> 00:23:21.908
My father is from Ugljan
and my mother from Vis.

00:23:21.932 --> 00:23:25.508
I have genes from Lika and
Bosnia and various other genes.

00:23:25.741 --> 00:23:30.322
But we used to go there; our whole
family always felt it was our own.

00:23:30.346 --> 00:23:35.825
I remember all four of us children returning
from Vis after two months of summer

00:23:35.863 --> 00:23:38.723
we all cried in the car
as if we were going to jail.

00:23:39.975 --> 00:23:47.188
About our roots, because of very difficult family
relationships, disputes, problems, and property

00:23:47.593 --> 00:23:49.766
It wasn't allowed to talk about it.

00:23:49.806 --> 00:23:53.802
I was really lost. And I remember, at 17

00:23:54.143 --> 00:23:59.428
I went alone for the first time with my
grandparents to the island of Ugljan.

00:24:00.149 --> 00:24:05.790
There, I spent time with my older
relatives, my grandfather's brothers.

00:24:06.917 --> 00:24:12.162
Before, it was boring for me, when older
people start playing cards and drinking a bit.

00:24:12.187 --> 00:24:17.708
We always found something more interesting,
but then, it was as if God opened my heart.

00:24:17.732 --> 00:24:23.668
I began to hear their heroic stories and the
suffering they endured for their faith in God.

00:24:23.692 --> 00:24:27.521
First was on Goli Otok for two
years, second was on Sveti Grgur.

00:24:27.545 --> 00:24:29.788
Third fled to Australia
and succeeded there.

00:24:29.812 --> 00:24:34.828
When they talked, I saw
strength and pride pouring into me.

00:24:35.447 --> 00:24:38.948
I felt so re-rooted again.

00:24:39.094 --> 00:24:44.228
We even slaughtered a lamb
there, as our male ritual

00:24:44.252 --> 00:24:47.507
which was unthinkable for a city kid.

00:24:47.531 --> 00:24:53.068
When I returned to Zagreb,
my mom didn't recognized me.

00:24:53.092 --> 00:24:56.148
She said: "You left as a
boy and returned as a man."

00:24:57.243 --> 00:25:04.793
It was just those three weeks in which I
realized and became proud of my roots.

00:25:05.712 --> 00:25:07.339
Genesis 12:8

00:25:08.466 --> 00:25:14.259
Abraham comes near a city
called Bethel, exactly there.

00:25:14.514 --> 00:25:24.317
"He went toward the hills east of Bethel and
pitched his tent, between Bethel and Ai.

00:25:25.079 --> 00:25:30.084
There he built an altar to the Lord
and called on the name of the Lord."

00:25:31.044 --> 00:25:34.308
A specific place,
remember it's about Bethel.

00:25:34.910 --> 00:25:39.868
His grandson Jacob didn't know about this.

00:25:40.517 --> 00:25:46.691
Jacob made a deceit. He received
his father's blessing by deception.

00:25:46.716 --> 00:25:51.673
His brother wants to kill him, and
he flees from him to his uncle Laban

00:25:52.351 --> 00:25:55.748
and he needs to spend the night somewhere.

00:26:01.819 --> 00:26:05.093
Genesis 28:10-19

00:26:05.879 --> 00:26:07.308
Jacob is fleeing.

00:26:07.333 --> 00:26:10.475
"Jacob left Beersheba
and set out for Harran.

00:26:10.499 --> 00:26:15.569
When he reached a certain place, he stopped
for the night because the sun had set.

00:26:15.593 --> 00:26:20.948
Taking one of the stones there, he put
it under his head and lay down to sleep.

00:26:21.583 --> 00:26:26.648
He had a dream in which he saw a
stairway resting on the earth, with its top

00:26:26.673 --> 00:26:31.076
reaching to heaven, and the angels
of God were ascending and descending on it.

00:26:31.101 --> 00:26:34.894
There above it stood the Lord"
- Listen what the Lord said to him.

00:26:34.918 --> 00:26:39.908
"I am the Lord, the God of your father
Abraham and the God of Isaac.

00:26:39.932 --> 00:26:43.775
I will give you and your descendants
the land on which you are lying.

00:26:43.808 --> 00:26:46.522
God appeared to him
exactly there for a reason.

00:26:46.878 --> 00:26:52.475
That is where his grandfather came and
invoked the name of God in that space.

00:26:53.801 --> 00:26:59.698
Many testimonies I've heard from you,
whom I know and whom I spiritually follow,

00:26:59.722 --> 00:27:05.043
that God has granted special graces
to you in these places where your ancestors

00:27:05.067 --> 00:27:09.528
invoked the Name of God, where they
suffered for Him, some even shed blood.

00:27:09.552 --> 00:27:12.462
And how many of these places are neglected?

00:27:14.348 --> 00:27:15.584
He says:

00:27:16.662 --> 00:27:19.978
"I will give you and your descendants
the land on which you are lying.

00:27:20.002 --> 00:27:24.997
Your descendants will be like the dust of the earth,
and you will spread out to the west and to the east,

00:27:25.021 --> 00:27:28.558
to the north and to the south. All peoples on earth
will be blessed through you and your offspring.

00:27:28.978 --> 00:27:32.501
I am with you and will watch
over you wherever you go

00:27:32.526 --> 00:27:35.068
I will bring you back to this land.

00:27:35.092 --> 00:27:39.365
I will not leave you until I have
done what I have promised you."

00:27:40.252 --> 00:27:45.548
When Jacob awoke from sleep, he thought: "Surely
 the Lord is in this place, and I was not aware of it."

00:27:45.572 --> 00:27:48.620
He was afraid and said,
"How awesome is this place!

00:27:48.644 --> 00:27:51.628
This is the house of
God, the gate of heaven."

00:27:51.849 --> 00:27:56.468
Then, in the text, we see that
it is precisely that city of Bethel.

00:27:56.492 --> 00:28:00.625
"Early the next morning Jacob took the
stone he had placed under his head.

00:28:00.649 --> 00:28:03.947
Set it up as a pillar
and poured oil on top of it.

00:28:03.972 --> 00:28:08.532
He called that place Bethel, though
the city used to be called Luz.

00:28:09.106 --> 00:28:15.741
God appears to him exactly in that place,
those were special places of grace for them.

00:28:16.145 --> 00:28:22.477
I could give you examples from the
books of Genesis and Exodus until midnight

00:28:22.501 --> 00:28:24.525
but I'll spare both you and myself.

00:28:24.833 --> 00:28:27.750
There are many examples in the Psalms too.

00:28:27.775 --> 00:28:34.187
We see how much their homeland meant to
the chosen people of Israel very precisely.

00:28:34.706 --> 00:28:38.868
Now we enter the New Testament,
and there are two streams.

00:28:40.881 --> 00:28:46.853
One of them wants to emphasize that it is
God's kingdom now, that we are all one now

00:28:46.877 --> 00:28:51.733
that the Church is actually that new
nation, and that this is not so important.

00:28:52.090 --> 00:28:54.653
What do you think?

00:28:55.368 --> 00:29:00.308
Jesus, who is our God and the main figure of
the New Testament, was He a patriot or not?

00:29:00.641 --> 00:29:03.117
Was Jesus a nationalist?

00:29:03.263 --> 00:29:08.173
Let's translate it, if Croatia and Israel
are playing, who would Jesus support?

00:29:14.761 --> 00:29:20.188
The Lord showed me two images when I was
praying about finding that healthy balance.

00:29:20.847 --> 00:29:24.428
Let's see what attitude Jesus
 had toward His homeland.

00:29:25.784 --> 00:29:28.891
Luke 19:41-43

00:29:29.383 --> 00:29:34.708
As he approached Jerusalem and saw
 the city, he wept over it and said:

00:29:35.406 --> 00:29:38.733
"If you, even you, had only known on
this day what would bring you peace-

00:29:38.758 --> 00:29:41.108
but now it is hidden from your eyes.

00:29:41.409 --> 00:29:46.250
The days will come upon you when your
enemies will build an embankment against you

00:29:46.274 --> 00:29:49.108
and encircle you and
hem you in on every side."

00:29:50.139 --> 00:29:53.268
I don't have to tell you what
Jerusalem means for the Jew.

00:29:53.299 --> 00:29:57.355
And we see Jesus coming, looking
at His city, and weeping over it.

00:29:57.681 --> 00:30:02.428
As God, He knows what will happen
and knows the cause that it's now hidden

00:30:02.453 --> 00:30:06.908
that God put a veil over the eyes of the people
of Israel so that they would not recognize Him

00:30:06.932 --> 00:30:10.515
so that the Gentiles could enter. As
God, He knows that, but He weeps.

00:30:11.467 --> 00:30:14.508
When I prayed about this in adoration

00:30:14.532 --> 00:30:19.051
it was like the Lord asked me
provocatively: Where else did I cry?

00:30:19.462 --> 00:30:24.723
There are two places in the Gospel where
Jesus wept. You probably know the other one.

00:30:25.858 --> 00:30:27.205
Lazarus' tomb.

00:30:27.823 --> 00:30:34.748
There is one very important detail.
It is the key to bringing our healthy attitude.

00:30:36.462 --> 00:30:43.286
Lazarus died, and Jesus was told about it.
He was then on a mission with His apostles.

00:30:43.668 --> 00:30:44.950
John 11: 11-15

00:30:44.975 --> 00:30:49.789
 "Our friend Lazarus has fallen asleep;
 but I am going there to wake him up.”

00:30:50.193 --> 00:30:53.650
His disciples replied:
“Lord, if he sleeps, he will get better.”

00:30:54.269 --> 00:30:59.701
Jesus had been speaking of his death, but
his disciples thought he meant natural sleep.

00:31:00.604 --> 00:31:02.722
Then He told them plainly:

00:31:02.746 --> 00:31:08.749
“Lazarus is dead, and for your sake I am glad
I was not there, so that you may believe.”

00:31:10.367 --> 00:31:15.228
Jesus, as God, knows
He will resurrect Lazarus.

00:31:16.323 --> 00:31:20.443
He knows He will do it.
 This happens earlier chronologically.

00:31:20.680 --> 00:31:24.775
He tells the disciples this before
even reaching Lazarus' house.

00:31:25.273 --> 00:31:27.628
Jesus approaches Lazarus' house.

00:31:27.652 --> 00:31:31.788
The processions meet Him, Lazarus's
sisters, Mary and Martha, come, weeping

00:31:31.813 --> 00:31:36.511
and now we see the last part,
which is important to draw a conclusion.

00:31:36.563 --> 00:31:43.270
"When Mary reached the place where Jesus was
and saw Him, she fell at His feet and said:

00:31:43.304 --> 00:31:47.216
'Lord, if you had been here,
my brother would not have died.'

00:31:47.732 --> 00:31:53.868
When Jesus saw her and the Jews weeping,
He was deeply moved in spirit and troubled.

00:31:53.892 --> 00:31:59.419
'Where have you laid him?' he asked.
'Come and see,' they replied.

00:32:00.312 --> 00:32:02.028
Jesus wept.

00:32:02.571 --> 00:32:05.865
Then the Jews said:
 "See how he loved him."

00:32:12.978 --> 00:32:18.702
Jesus is the only one who was in himself,
entirely God and entirely man.

00:32:19.495 --> 00:32:25.409
We see that even in those situations when
He, as God, knows why the people of Jerusalem

00:32:25.433 --> 00:32:30.940
can't recognize his coming and knows that
He will raise Lazarus, He as a man weeps.

00:32:31.376 --> 00:32:37.897
From this, we can see that Jesus, in his human
dimension, was indeed a passionate patriot

00:32:38.332 --> 00:32:40.948
who knew how to love his people.

00:32:42.660 --> 00:32:51.056
We see that the New Testament provides a
biblical basis for the healthy patriotism.

00:32:51.081 --> 00:32:56.580
Let's move on, not just focusing
on Jesus because he is still God and man

00:32:56.850 --> 00:33:01.904
Let's see further through the apostles. E.g.
I deliberately chose provocative St. Paul

00:33:01.966 --> 00:33:04.524
Many call him the initiator of globalization

00:33:04.570 --> 00:33:08.165
Galatians 3:28
He says there is no longer Jew or Greek.

00:33:08.189 --> 00:33:10.268
All that is irrelevant.
We are all one.

00:33:10.292 --> 00:33:14.548
Even in that line, he says
there is no longer a male or female.

00:33:14.572 --> 00:33:18.053
So they say Paul was
LGBT-friendly. Yeah, right.

00:33:19.666 --> 00:33:21.468
Philippians 3:20

00:33:21.492 --> 00:33:23.970
But our citizenship is in heaven.

00:33:24.299 --> 00:33:28.788
And we eagerly await a Savior
from there, the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:33:28.812 --> 00:33:34.788
From these lines, we can see Paul
as a man who is already above.

00:33:36.786 --> 00:33:40.365
However, do not read the Bible
 as Satan quotes it to Jesus.

00:33:40.897 --> 00:33:47.486
Do not, like fundamentalists, extract
one line and ignore all other contexts.

00:33:47.978 --> 00:33:50.953
Let's see what Paul was like in general.

00:33:50.977 --> 00:33:54.963
Undoubtedly, the focus of our
actions should be on the heavens.

00:33:57.040 --> 00:33:59.293
Romans 9:1-5

00:34:00.792 --> 00:34:05.097
Consider Paul wrote the Epistle
 to the Romans as an old man.

00:34:05.121 --> 00:34:10.968
even though it is the first Epistle in the
Holy Scriptures attributed to St Paul

00:34:10.993 --> 00:34:13.598
he wrote it last while
awaiting martyrdom.

00:34:13.622 --> 00:34:16.768
You know that Paul
died in Rome, that he was martyred.

00:34:17.821 --> 00:34:22.868
He said: "I speak the truth
in Christ, I am not lying

00:34:22.893 --> 00:34:26.808
my conscience confirms it
through the Holy Spirit.

00:34:26.897 --> 00:34:30.063
When you see a sentence
 like this in Paul's texts

00:34:30.088 --> 00:34:36.683
you know that the following is very offensive,
 but he wants to emphasize that it is indeed so.

00:34:37.355 --> 00:34:40.428
That is why he first said:
"I speak the truth, I am not lying.

00:34:40.452 --> 00:34:44.130
I speak the truth in Christ"
 This is not his truth.

00:34:44.383 --> 00:34:46.707
My conscience is my co-witness.

00:34:46.732 --> 00:34:52.331
But not my, which may be wrongly formed,
but my conscience in the Holy Spirit.

00:34:53.004 --> 00:34:57.348
"I have great sorrow and
unceasing anguish in my heart"

00:34:57.372 --> 00:34:59.722
Paul continuously suffered because of this

00:34:59.919 --> 00:35:04.628
"For I could wish that I myself
were cursed and cut off from Christ

00:35:04.652 --> 00:35:08.277
for the sake of my people,
 those of my own race."

00:35:08.670 --> 00:35:14.748
Imagine when Paul, who knows very well
what it means to be separated from Christ

00:35:14.772 --> 00:35:18.588
It's not like when the BBB sings
"and to heaven with him and to hell"

00:35:18.612 --> 00:35:20.788
and have no idea what heaven or hell is

00:35:20.835 --> 00:35:23.091
St Paul knew very well

00:35:23.409 --> 00:35:27.326
He says he isn't lying and that his
conscience in the Holy Spirit is his witness

00:35:28.800 --> 00:35:35.251
"I would agree to be accursed, for eternity,
if only my countrymen according to the flesh

00:35:35.284 --> 00:35:42.385
Israelites, Jews, had converted and
recognized what was for their salvation.

00:35:42.418 --> 00:35:48.796
"Theirs is the adoption to sonship, the divine glory, the covenants,
 the receiving of the law, the temple worship and the promises.

00:35:48.820 --> 00:35:54.555
Theirs are the patriarchs, and from them is traced the human
ancestry of the Messiah, who is God over all, forever praised! Amen."

00:35:55.023 --> 00:36:00.268
We see how passionate
Paul was as a patriot.

00:36:00.767 --> 00:36:05.188
Be cautious with the things
being served to you now

00:36:05.311 --> 00:36:09.208
unfortunately, often even
in religious education.

00:36:09.692 --> 00:36:12.104
Take a healthy biblical standpoint.

00:36:12.128 --> 00:36:15.977
I could go on,
but time isn't on our side.

00:36:17.176 --> 00:36:20.496
We've seen numerous examples
in the New Testament.

00:36:20.527 --> 00:36:24.428
We also have examples among saints. Look at
this quote from Blessed Alojzije Stepinac.

00:36:24.729 --> 00:36:29.432
"In love for the Croatian people, I will not
allow myself to be overshadowed by anyone."

00:36:29.456 --> 00:36:34.668
Throughout the history of the Church this
attitude was regularly cultivated by the saints.

00:36:34.692 --> 00:36:37.238
So, it is healthy.

00:36:38.815 --> 00:36:43.247
Also, Blessed Alojzije Stepinac

00:36:44.236 --> 00:36:47.279
when it was necessary to
confront the Ustasha regime

00:36:47.321 --> 00:36:53.865
precisely because it was killing
other people due to nationalism

00:36:53.890 --> 00:36:58.348
that same Stepinac was the only
one who had the courage to do it.

00:36:58.372 --> 00:37:01.531
This is a wonderful sermon
on the Feast of Christ the King.

00:37:01.555 --> 00:37:04.428
Try to find it on the
Internet and read it all.

00:37:04.452 --> 00:37:10.748
You should had the guts to say
this in 1942 in Zagreb Cathedral.

00:37:11.365 --> 00:37:16.472
It's a brilliant text; try to find
it online; you have the whole text.

00:37:16.523 --> 00:37:23.547
He speaks about that
national diversity and says:

00:37:23.572 --> 00:37:27.971
That diversity must not be
a source of mutual destruction.

00:37:28.003 --> 00:37:33.308
Because the third thing we claim is that every
 nation and race, as they are formed on earth today

00:37:33.332 --> 00:37:37.506
have the right to a life and a
treatment worthy of a human being.

00:37:37.531 --> 00:37:41.828
All of them, regardless of whether they
belong to the Gypsy race or any other,

00:37:41.852 --> 00:37:46.508
whether they are black or classy Europeans,
whether they are hated Jews or proud Aryans,

00:37:46.532 --> 00:37:50.706
have the same right to say
Our Father who is in heaven.

00:37:50.955 --> 00:37:55.304
If God has granted this right to everyone,
what human authority can deny it?

00:37:55.572 --> 00:38:00.348
All nations, have an equal obligation
to beat their chests and say,

00:38:00.372 --> 00:38:05.093
forgive us our debts
 as we forgive our debtors.

00:38:05.117 --> 00:38:09.709
That's why the Catholic Church
has always and still condemns every

00:38:09.733 --> 00:38:14.111
injustice and violence committed in the
name of class, race, or ethnic theories.

00:38:14.136 --> 00:38:18.529
Intelligence can't be eradicated because
it pleases the working class,

00:38:18.691 --> 00:38:20.707
as taught by Bolshevism.

00:38:20.884 --> 00:38:26.123
Gypsies or Jews cannot be eradicated
 because they are considered an inferior race.

00:38:26.275 --> 00:38:31.549
Back then, the term gypsies was used, so don't
think I'm offending the Roma national minority

00:38:31.573 --> 00:38:34.190
I'm reading how Stepinac spoke then.

00:38:35.419 --> 00:38:41.668
He concludes: " If the principles of racial
theories that have no basis are applied lightly,

00:38:41.692 --> 00:38:45.908
is there even any security left
 on earth for any nation?"

00:38:45.933 --> 00:38:50.709
You can imagine that Pavelić didn't
particularly like Stepinac after this.

00:38:50.810 --> 00:38:55.978
However, his charisma was too strong to
remove him. This is our role model.

00:38:56.002 --> 00:38:59.989
Pope John Paul II says:" The brightest
 figure of the Croatian church

00:39:00.013 --> 00:39:03.107
whom we should follow
in very challenging times."

00:39:03.214 --> 00:39:10.902
The times ahead are very challenging,
 but it's not the first time for us.

00:39:10.927 --> 00:39:16.633
We often like to proclaim that our times are
harder than before, but I'm not quite sure.

00:39:16.658 --> 00:39:21.758
It has always been demanding for those who
were God's; the world was always against them.

00:39:21.784 --> 00:39:23.821
But they have triumphed in it.

00:39:27.135 --> 00:39:31.096
That's why a healthy attitude is:

00:39:32.442 --> 00:39:35.948
our direction is Heaven,
the heavenly homeland.

00:39:36.723 --> 00:39:42.807
That is our goal, and the path is this
earthly homeland. We can't exclude either.

00:39:42.844 --> 00:39:48.868
St Paul gives us a brilliant
distinction in the 1 Corinthians

00:39:48.892 --> 00:39:52.651
so that we know what must come
first and then what comes next.

00:39:52.676 --> 00:39:55.092
We are born in this earthly homeland.

00:39:57.322 --> 00:40:00.648
We dream and fight for the one above.

00:40:00.672 --> 00:40:05.781
But, as I said, this is the goal, and this is
the path, and they do not exclude each other.

00:40:06.316 --> 00:40:10.668
1 Corinthians 15:42-49

00:40:11.659 --> 00:40:16.827
"So will it be with the resurrection of the dead. The body
that is sown is perishable, it is raised imperishable

00:40:16.852 --> 00:40:22.748
it is sown in dishonor, it is raised in glory;
it is sown in weakness, it is raised in power

00:40:22.812 --> 00:40:26.422
it is sown a natural body,
it is raised a spiritual body.

00:40:26.446 --> 00:40:28.926
If there is a natural body,
there is also a spiritual body.

00:40:29.412 --> 00:40:32.905
So it is written: “The first man
Adam became a living being;

00:40:32.929 --> 00:40:35.256
the last Adam, a life-giving spirit."

00:40:35.280 --> 00:40:39.746
The spiritual did not come first, but
the natural, and after that the spiritual.

00:40:39.818 --> 00:40:43.988
That is the attitude we should nurture.

00:40:44.019 --> 00:40:48.957
This is my observation,
and I found confirmation

00:40:48.981 --> 00:40:52.348
from one of the most influential
doctors of the 20th century

00:40:52.372 --> 00:40:58.148
the author of that individual
approach in psychoanalysis

00:40:58.173 --> 00:41:03.994
and he also related physical illnesses with
specific psychological and spiritual states.

00:41:04.019 --> 00:41:08.650
Today, it's something normal, and we
know it as a psychosomatic disorder

00:41:08.674 --> 00:41:11.868
Paul Tournier, I don't know
if you've heard of him.

00:41:11.892 --> 00:41:16.505
A great thinker and one of the most
influential doctors of the twentieth century.

00:41:16.530 --> 00:41:24.047
He brings an interesting thesis that
these two extremes can only be avoided,

00:41:24.072 --> 00:41:27.762
this is a man who has experience
from all faiths, nations, religions

00:41:27.786 --> 00:41:31.134
and patients all over the world

00:41:31.393 --> 00:41:36.628
he says that these two
extremes can only be reconciled

00:41:36.652 --> 00:41:40.355
in individuals who live
 an authentic Christian faith.

00:41:40.379 --> 00:41:44.322
I will quote him.
It will sound even more powerful.

00:41:45.242 --> 00:41:49.714
He describes these two poles that
constantly put humanity in conflict.

00:41:49.747 --> 00:41:55.548
"It is a common experience for humanity to oscillate
between two poles: simplicity and complexity."

00:41:55.572 --> 00:42:01.679
People whose minds are such that they see only one
side of something tend to take decisive action.

00:42:01.703 --> 00:42:06.068
They succeed in everything they
do because they don't hairsplitting

00:42:06.092 --> 00:42:09.158
and have abundant trust
 in their own abilities.

00:42:09.183 --> 00:42:13.548
While individuals with
refined and cultivated minds

00:42:13.572 --> 00:42:16.091
tend to get lost in the
maze of subtle distinctions.

00:42:16.115 --> 00:42:21.948
They always see how complicated things really are,
so their powers of persuasion are negligible.

00:42:21.972 --> 00:42:25.334
Have you ever wondered why
people who are so raw, often primitive

00:42:25.358 --> 00:42:27.886
always rise to leadership positions?

00:42:28.255 --> 00:42:32.938
I have nothing against those
people, but uneducated people

00:42:32.962 --> 00:42:36.817
emerge and learn to
manage just because of this.

00:42:37.557 --> 00:42:42.579
And some who sound so admirable,
you could listen to them for hours

00:42:42.795 --> 00:42:45.400
but let them something
to manage, they fail.

00:42:46.185 --> 00:42:51.814
He continues: "That's why the world
 is led by those least suited

00:42:51.854 --> 00:42:55.516
to raise its cultural and moral standards.

00:42:56.154 --> 00:43:01.482
Only a few manage to combine both
tendencies. He says that is extremely rare.

00:43:01.507 --> 00:43:08.154
By my understanding, to fulfill this wonder, the
best prerequisite is a living Christian faith

00:43:08.265 --> 00:43:12.675
because it provides both deep
understanding and simplicity of heart.

00:43:12.700 --> 00:43:15.143
That's why I appeal to you:

00:43:15.167 --> 00:43:19.128
You must be elite who will bring
healthy balance - that Stepinac brought.

00:43:19.899 --> 00:43:22.574
I won't let myself be
overshadowed in love for Croatia,

00:43:22.598 --> 00:43:26.403
but I will never allow
trampling others’ rights

00:43:27.212 --> 00:43:31.565
Only someone who authentically
 lived his Christianity

00:43:31.589 --> 00:43:35.486
could bring such a healthy attitude that
we can still be proud of today.

00:43:37.097 --> 00:43:40.724
That's why you have a great
responsibility. You are a lighthouse.

00:43:41.466 --> 00:43:44.951
People around you are falling
into one of these two extremes.

00:43:44.975 --> 00:43:47.635
Without offending them.

00:43:47.659 --> 00:43:52.361
We would also be like that without the Holy
Spirit, but our responsibility is bigger.

00:43:57.100 --> 00:44:01.150
We are entering another very tricky area

00:44:01.175 --> 00:44:09.048
How to nurture healthy and biblically
 oriented patriotism and live it

00:44:10.490 --> 00:44:12.468
The Pope gives us the answer again.

00:44:14.205 --> 00:44:18.203
We need to nurture collective,
familial, and national memory.

00:44:19.359 --> 00:44:27.145
I will advertise another excellent
book by Pope Francis - "On Education"

00:44:28.050 --> 00:44:33.659
in which he discusses the
issue of educating young people

00:44:33.684 --> 00:44:37.107
to have a healthy
attitude toward patriotism.

00:44:37.132 --> 00:44:41.279
He says: We cannot educate if we
separate ourselves from memory.

00:44:41.385 --> 00:44:46.327
Therefore, let us ask for the grace to renew
memories-memories of our personal journey

00:44:46.351 --> 00:44:48.898
how the Lord sought us

00:44:48.932 --> 00:44:55.041
memories of my religious family, our educational
communities, and memories as a nation.

00:44:55.065 --> 00:44:59.967
Looking back is an awakening to
receive God's word even more strongly.

00:45:00.864 --> 00:45:06.188
You know, the Israelites, Jews, when they
go into battle, what do they say first?

00:45:07.069 --> 00:45:12.445
O YHWH, who saved our forefather Abraham,
who led Moses, who parted the Red Sea

00:45:12.470 --> 00:45:15.916
they recount these God's
victories, and then they win

00:45:16.297 --> 00:45:19.497
knowing it’s the same
God who did all of that

00:45:20.720 --> 00:45:23.165
Memory is active, not passive.

00:45:23.189 --> 00:45:26.748
In the Hebrew way of thinking,
remembrance always prompts action.

00:45:27.246 --> 00:45:33.948
In some translations, "YHWH will remember us"
is translated as "YHWH will intercede for us"

00:45:33.973 --> 00:45:36.428
Literally, it is a synonym.

00:45:36.983 --> 00:45:41.713
So we see that it is active,
something that we need to nurture.

00:45:42.213 --> 00:45:47.228
Pope continues: "Nations have
memories as well as individuals."

00:45:47.252 --> 00:45:50.524
"Humanity also has a collective memory."

00:45:51.424 --> 00:45:54.302
Remember those earlier days
after you had received the light,

00:45:54.326 --> 00:45:57.278
when you endured in a great
conflict full of suffering. Hebrews 10:32

00:45:57.303 --> 00:46:00.854
Remember your leaders, who
spoke the word of God to you.

00:46:00.878 --> 00:46:05.109
Consider the outcome of their way of
life and imitate their faith. Hebrews 13:7

00:46:06.042 --> 00:46:10.908
Why? This is very important now, to
remain united and to know how to resist

00:46:10.932 --> 00:46:15.781
the wave of globalization that is coming
and wants to denationalize nations.

00:46:16.844 --> 00:46:20.948
(Pope Francis: "On Education")
"Memory has the power of unification and integration."

00:46:20.972 --> 00:46:24.548
"While intellect left to itself
pushes a person into the abyss,

00:46:24.572 --> 00:46:28.258
memory becomes the living
nucleus of a family or nation."

00:46:28.607 --> 00:46:32.348
"A family without memory
does not deserve to be called so."

00:46:32.372 --> 00:46:38.388
"A family that doesn't respect and take care of
its elders, who are its living memory, is a broken family."

00:46:38.412 --> 00:46:43.395
"But a family and a nation that remember
are a family and a nation with a future."

00:46:43.420 --> 00:46:48.188
Pope appeals, especially to people
working in the educational system.

00:46:48.213 --> 00:46:52.005
"Let's not allow the elites,
separated from reality,

00:46:52.029 --> 00:46:55.423
to try to diminish or
undermine this living memory."

00:46:55.448 --> 00:47:00.428
"On the contrary, let us turn to those
precious, moral, and religious sources

00:47:00.452 --> 00:47:06.010
of the faithful people of God
to nourish and heal our institutions.

00:47:06.795 --> 00:47:12.308
This is very, very important. And our
memory is being taken away from us.

00:47:13.290 --> 00:47:18.115
E.g. the Homeland War, which is
the basis of the creation of our state

00:47:18.147 --> 00:47:22.148
is discussed in the fourth grade,
when the national exams are held.

00:47:22.172 --> 00:47:24.668
I haven't heard a single hour about it,

00:47:24.692 --> 00:47:28.500
nor the young people I'm talking
to now know nothing about it.

00:47:29.230 --> 00:47:30.559
That was recent

00:47:30.584 --> 00:47:32.807
someone was shedding blood or dying,

00:47:32.831 --> 00:47:36.861
but generations are being raised
 who don't care about that.

00:47:37.677 --> 00:47:43.771
And it will be retaliation for them. That's
why the key is in nurturing that memory.

00:47:44.570 --> 00:47:49.913
Look how many times in the Old Testament
God encourages the people with this verb.

00:47:49.937 --> 00:47:52.430
I'll give you just a few examples.

00:47:52.454 --> 00:47:54.628
Deuteronomy 8: 2-6.

00:47:54.653 --> 00:47:57.868
"Remember how the Lord
led you in the wilderness,

00:47:57.892 --> 00:48:01.063
to humble and test you in order
to know what was in your heart.

00:48:01.172 --> 00:48:02.859
Deuteronomy 4:9.

00:48:02.884 --> 00:48:08.228
"Be careful and watch yourselves closely so that you do
not forget the things your eyes have seen or let them

00:48:08.274 --> 00:48:11.738
fade from your heart as long as you live.

00:48:11.762 --> 00:48:14.801
Teach them to your children
and to their children after them."

00:48:14.826 --> 00:48:17.839
What's the problem?

00:48:18.057 --> 00:48:22.515
The problem is that when we lose memory,
we necessarily begin to rely on idols.

00:48:23.236 --> 00:48:25.434
And this is happening to our nation.

00:48:26.302 --> 00:48:31.911
If you don't have the memory you nurtured, you
will necessarily need something to hold onto.

00:48:34.240 --> 00:48:38.316
That's what the Pope says:
"Whoever has no memory relies on idols."

00:48:38.372 --> 00:48:40.157
Deut 28:47.

00:48:40.182 --> 00:48:46.588
"Because you didn't serve the Lord joyfully
and gladly in the time of prosperity,

00:48:46.612 --> 00:48:48.972
therefore you will serve the enemies."

00:48:49.942 --> 00:48:53.735
Deut 4:25-31.

00:49:06.604 --> 00:49:09.628
When the blessings come,
and everything goes well,

00:49:09.652 --> 00:49:14.198
whether we admit it to ourselves
or not, we live in that time.

00:49:14.223 --> 00:49:17.348
No matter how much we like
to say that it's hard for us,

00:49:17.373 --> 00:49:20.268
look a few generations
back at how they lived,

00:49:20.292 --> 00:49:24.511
what they ate and wore,
how mobile they were.

00:49:25.332 --> 00:49:27.813
Then this temptation happens.

00:49:27.838 --> 00:49:33.348
"After you have had children and grandchildren
and have lived in the land a long time

00:49:33.373 --> 00:49:36.948
if you then become corrupt
and make any kind of idol,

00:49:36.972 --> 00:49:41.667
doing evil in the eyes of the Lord
your God and arousing his anger

00:49:41.692 --> 00:49:44.708
I call the heavens and the
earth as witnesses against you

00:49:44.732 --> 00:49:48.988
that you will quickly perish from the land
that you are crossing the Jordan to possess.

00:49:49.012 --> 00:49:53.210
You will not live there long
but will certainly be destroyed.

00:49:53.235 --> 00:49:55.388
The Lord will scatter you among the peoples

00:49:55.412 --> 00:49:59.388
and only a few of you will survive among
the nations to which the Lord will drive you.

00:49:59.413 --> 00:50:04.520
There you will worship
man-made gods of wood and stone

00:50:04.544 --> 00:50:08.711
which cannot see or hear or eat or smell."

00:50:08.814 --> 00:50:12.825
This is exactly what happened
to our nation. Things started well for us.

00:50:12.850 --> 00:50:15.388
We entered the European Union, great.

00:50:16.531 --> 00:50:19.254
And 400,000 people left.

00:50:19.505 --> 00:50:24.111
My people, are you aware that
without God's miracle, that's irreversible?

00:50:27.290 --> 00:50:34.861
And there, where they are,
without naming anyone, across the border,

00:50:35.004 --> 00:50:42.064
they will worship gods made by human
hands, gods of tin, and gods of paper.

00:50:42.693 --> 00:50:43.941
It's terrible.

00:50:44.997 --> 00:50:50.674
I don't want to call anyone out ad hominem
here. I know someone had good reasons

00:50:50.698 --> 00:50:55.423
but I want to shed some biblical light
on how God sees this phenomenon.

00:50:58.939 --> 00:51:03.963
Someone was dying and bleeding, and
someone else sold it and left so easily

00:51:03.987 --> 00:51:10.308
bought a car with that money, wrecked it.
Now he is in debt and has nothing of his own.

00:51:11.983 --> 00:51:13.628
Isn't that a curse?

00:51:14.738 --> 00:51:18.659
Come on, you tell me,
maybe I'm a bit delusional about this.

00:51:18.692 --> 00:51:22.210
How would you call it?
What does the Holy Scripture say?

00:51:23.915 --> 00:51:25.816
If we do not preserve the memory

00:51:25.840 --> 00:51:30.111
we will start worshiping idols,
whether we admit it to ourselves or not.

00:51:32.272 --> 00:51:38.412
Marino Restrepo, my good friend,
when he started his ministry,

00:51:38.437 --> 00:51:41.373
he prayed for the strongest
protection when he went to Africa.

00:51:41.397 --> 00:51:47.902
Everyone told him that there were all kinds of
witchcrafs and voodoo targeted at preachers.

00:51:48.227 --> 00:51:52.571
You know what he realized? Those sorceresses
aren't that dangerous at all; they don't know.

00:51:52.595 --> 00:51:55.845
When they see who Christ
is, they hand over their

00:51:55.869 --> 00:52:00.174
charms, amulets, and
talismans and ask to be baptized.

00:52:00.927 --> 00:52:04.472
He says, now, after 40 years of experience

00:52:05.400 --> 00:52:09.309
"I pray most strongly when I go to
Western Europe and North America.

00:52:09.333 --> 00:52:15.428
Because the spirit of materialism most
effectively prevents the spread of the Word"

00:52:16.340 --> 00:52:20.348
Be cautious and take this very seriously.

00:52:27.924 --> 00:52:31.388
Talk to your family
about your family history

00:52:31.546 --> 00:52:35.093
visit the places you come from.

00:52:37.082 --> 00:52:38.908
Renew if you can.

00:52:40.586 --> 00:52:42.288
Preserve the memory of it.

00:52:44.097 --> 00:52:49.703
We must be grateful to those who
made it possible for us to be alive today.

00:52:50.092 --> 00:52:52.669
Ante Čaljkušić said it brilliantly.

00:52:52.693 --> 00:52:56.588
When a woman aborts, she hasn't
 just aborted that child,

00:52:56.612 --> 00:53:00.828
but maybe 1,000 offspring
that would be born later from that child.

00:53:00.852 --> 00:53:06.671
And you are here, a miracle of God. Why?
Because your ancestors gave you life and God.

00:53:07.875 --> 00:53:12.073
Now we're entering the third area

00:53:12.644 --> 00:53:14.494
I'm in timing.

00:53:16.435 --> 00:53:19.070
3. Why and how to pray for the ancestors?

00:53:20.244 --> 00:53:22.895
Why don't people preserve memory?

00:53:22.920 --> 00:53:30.165
We have to understand that memory is
very difficult, whether national or familial.

00:53:30.189 --> 00:53:36.536
In Bosnia and Herzegovina are many parishes
in exile,and it's hard to even mentally go back.

00:53:36.561 --> 00:53:39.174
I would dare say that without
the Holy Spirit, it's impossible.

00:53:39.199 --> 00:53:47.325
Just look at the names Catholics gave. I've
traveled it up and down all the dirt roads.

00:53:47.696 --> 00:53:54.847
Čemerno, Zla vlast, Zlopolje. Išćelišće.
Odselišće, meaning sorrow, harm, and exodus.

00:53:54.888 --> 00:54:02.433
Why? Well, history was like that.
How to love Čemerno (Sorrowfully)

00:54:03.818 --> 00:54:09.626
The history was brutal. Or people who
come and talk about their family history,

00:54:10.400 --> 00:54:16.160
which is so difficult due to
property, infidelities, and divorces.

00:54:16.184 --> 00:54:18.068
They can't stand their parents.

00:54:18.092 --> 00:54:21.570
They forgive because the Bible says so,
but it's not even close to their hearts.

00:54:21.609 --> 00:54:28.145
We see that there is a need for prayer
for reconciliation with our ancestors

00:54:30.260 --> 00:54:33.588
and with our homeland,
the place we come from.

00:54:33.612 --> 00:54:37.639
I won't discuss this second part because you
have the theme of memory and reconciliation.

00:54:37.663 --> 00:54:42.992
We've talked a lot about it, but first
part is especially relevant today.

00:54:43.016 --> 00:54:49.883
In November, we pray for the deceased,
and then you have those discussions.

00:54:49.907 --> 00:54:52.907
Does the sin of our
ancestors impact us or not?

00:54:52.932 --> 00:54:56.828
You'll hear from various pulpits:
No, baptism erases everything.

00:54:56.853 --> 00:55:03.147
Others say: Yes, we pray for the purification of
the family tree and some strange terminologies.

00:55:03.172 --> 00:55:04.999
We have to find that healthy balance.

00:55:05.023 --> 00:55:09.337
Do you think we engage in
this because it's fun for us?

00:55:09.362 --> 00:55:12.664
It's because people
come out of genuine need.

00:55:13.053 --> 00:55:22.330
You can wait for the Church to develop a very
 clear set of rules and then enter into this.

00:55:22.995 --> 00:55:25.188
I respect people who see it that way.

00:55:25.489 --> 00:55:31.866
But what would happen if we approached
all mystical phenomena like that?

00:55:32.063 --> 00:55:36.495
Some people don't want to go to Medjugorje
until the Church officially recognizes it.

00:55:36.519 --> 00:55:37.818
Today, it's a shrine

00:55:37.847 --> 00:55:40.938
I respect that, and I'm not criticizing.
Thank God.

00:55:41.684 --> 00:55:44.548
However, imagine that everyone
 looked at it that way.

00:55:45.296 --> 00:55:50.899
There have been officially
2,000 spiritual vocations from Medjugorje.

00:55:51.186 --> 00:55:53.960
They received a spiritual
vocation in Medjugorje.

00:55:54.007 --> 00:55:59.667
While based on the letters that
Franciscans received, there are 7,000 of them.

00:55:59.893 --> 00:56:04.427
Priests, who are very active
in spiritual renewals and confessions

00:56:04.452 --> 00:56:07.731
say that every other conversion
 is related to Medjugorje.

00:56:08.076 --> 00:56:12.148
We can wait or, respect
what the Church also respects,

00:56:12.172 --> 00:56:15.322
the sensus fidei, the
feeling among the people.

00:56:15.571 --> 00:56:21.571
Why, even before Stepinac was beatified,
his grave was visited all day by the people?

00:56:21.595 --> 00:56:23.582
Because he attracts.

00:56:25.084 --> 00:56:30.206
The same here; we can wait,
listen, and be very cautious

00:56:30.230 --> 00:56:31.665
but there are concrete problems.

00:56:31.712 --> 00:56:35.412
People whom I spiritually
guide were healed from

00:56:35.436 --> 00:56:39.100
incurable diseases when they
prayed correctly for their ancestors.

00:56:39.202 --> 00:56:42.779
Let's dive into doctrine a bit;
what does doctrine say?

00:56:44.311 --> 00:56:47.628
The Catechism of
the Catholic Church, point 404.

00:56:48.516 --> 00:56:52.508
Original sin, which is
sin in an analogous way.

00:56:52.532 --> 00:56:56.548
It is not something we have done directly

00:56:58.499 --> 00:57:02.153
but sin in an analogous way.
It says this about original sin.

00:57:02.258 --> 00:57:05.479
It is a sin which will be transmitted
by propagation to all mankind,

00:57:05.503 --> 00:57:09.307
by the transmission of a human nature
deprived of original holiness and justice.

00:57:09.689 --> 00:57:13.788
That is why original sin is called
"sin" only in an analogical sense:

00:57:13.812 --> 00:57:18.437
it is a sin "contracted" and
not "committed" - a state and not an act.

00:57:18.743 --> 00:57:23.188
If we are affected by the sin
of our first parents, Adam and Eve

00:57:23.212 --> 00:57:27.770
do you really think that you will not be
affected by the sins of your parents?

00:57:28.619 --> 00:57:32.831
Therein lies the problem with those
who say that baptism erases everything

00:57:33.917 --> 00:57:38.512
as if baptism is a magical act,
 bioenergy, hocus pocus.

00:57:39.917 --> 00:57:43.708
It is true that after baptism,
 we no longer have moral guilt.

00:57:44.335 --> 00:57:50.588
But baptism is a covenant like any sacrament.
 Those of us who are married, you all know.

00:57:51.348 --> 00:57:54.713
Since marriage is also a covenant

00:57:54.757 --> 00:58:00.452
does that mean that the moment you get
married, all the problems disappear?

00:58:00.476 --> 00:58:05.036
Do you live happily ever after?
Not quite.

00:58:05.782 --> 00:58:10.028
Because every covenant
has to be fought for

00:58:10.052 --> 00:58:14.140
you have to die to
yourself for that covenant.

00:58:15.386 --> 00:58:19.618
The Catechism of the Catholic Church
 also confirms this.

00:58:20.333 --> 00:58:22.320
Point 1263

00:58:22.447 --> 00:58:24.715
By Baptism all sins are forgiven,

00:58:24.739 --> 00:58:28.533
original sin and all personal sins,
as well as all punishment for sin.

00:58:28.866 --> 00:58:34.604
In those who have been reborn nothing remains that
would impede their entry into the Kingdom of God

00:58:34.628 --> 00:58:38.028
neither Adam's sin, nor personal
sin, nor the consequences of sin,

00:58:38.052 --> 00:58:40.671
the gravest of which
is separation from God.

00:58:40.813 --> 00:58:46.619
And here most of them stop, but it's the same
 as the temptation of Jesus in the desert.

00:58:46.690 --> 00:58:52.452
The devil says it's written, throw yourself
down, but Jesus says: Yes, but it's also written

00:58:52.484 --> 00:58:54.539
in Catholicism 1264

00:58:54.698 --> 00:59:00.867
Yet certain temporal consequences of sin remain
in the baptized, such as suffering, illness, death

00:59:00.891 --> 00:59:06.074
and such frailties inherent in life as weaknesses
of character, as well as an inclination to sin

00:59:06.098 --> 00:59:10.860
that Tradition calls concupiscence, or
metaphorically, "the tinder for sin" (fomes peccati)

00:59:10.962 --> 00:59:14.102
since concupiscence
"is left for us to wrestle with

00:59:14.126 --> 00:59:20.053
it cannot harm those who do not consent but
manfully resist it by the grace of Jesus Christ."

00:59:20.078 --> 00:59:26.468
So, it calls us to fight for it, and
that's why it's quite justified to pray

00:59:26.492 --> 00:59:29.508
for the reparation for
the sins of our ancestors.

00:59:29.532 --> 00:59:33.974
Because then they will experience grace.
They can no longer change what they did,

00:59:33.998 --> 00:59:37.769
but we can deliver them from the
place of torment with our prayers.

00:59:37.793 --> 00:59:41.588
It will also be a great
blessing for our lives.

00:59:41.698 --> 00:59:46.999
This is very biblically based. I'll skim
through the Old and New Testament a bit.

00:59:47.023 --> 00:59:50.855
Exodus 34:6. “The Lord, the
compassionate and gracious God,

00:59:50.879 --> 00:59:53.868
slow to anger, abounding
in love and faithfulness,

00:59:53.892 --> 00:59:58.188
maintaining love to thousands, and
forgiving wickedness, rebellion and sin.

00:59:58.212 --> 01:00:00.382
Yet he does not leave the guilty unpunished

01:00:00.407 --> 01:00:02.686
he punishes the children and their children

01:00:02.710 --> 01:00:05.522
for the sin of the parents to
the third and fourth generation.”

01:00:05.910 --> 01:00:10.988
Lamentations 5:7. Our ancestors sinned and
are no more, and we bear their punishment.

01:00:11.067 --> 01:00:14.186
Now, we come to the most
controversial text, Ezekiel.

01:00:14.211 --> 01:00:19.570
Those who advocate the thesis that there is
no sin of the ancestors, that it is nonsense.

01:00:19.694 --> 01:00:23.927
So that it's not just me lecturing

01:00:25.958 --> 01:00:29.579
Ezekiel 18.

01:00:33.498 --> 01:00:36.739
The word of the Lord came to me:

01:00:36.771 --> 01:00:39.693
"What do you people mean
 by quoting this proverb:

01:00:39.717 --> 01:00:42.778
" The parents eat sour grapes, and
the children's teeth are set on edge'? "

01:00:42.803 --> 01:00:47.148
As surely as I live, declares the Sovereign Lord,
 you will no longer quote this proverb in Israel.

01:00:47.172 --> 01:00:51.468
For everyone belongs to me, the parent as
well as the child—both alike belong to me.

01:00:51.690 --> 01:00:55.961
The one who sins is the one who will die.
So it says this will not be said anymore.

01:00:55.986 --> 01:00:59.956
But Ezekiel clearly shows
when it won't, it says:

01:00:59.981 --> 01:01:03.228
But suppose this son has a son who
sees all the sins his father commits

01:01:03.252 --> 01:01:07.455
and though he sees them,
he does not do such things:

01:01:07.479 --> 01:01:13.461
He does not eat at the mountain
shrines or look to the idols of Israel.

01:01:13.500 --> 01:01:18.836
Does not defile his neighbor's wife. He does
not oppress anyone or require a pledge for a loan.

01:01:18.861 --> 01:01:21.443
This describes a holy life!

01:01:21.594 --> 01:01:26.228
so if you start living a holy life, then
the spiritual law will not continue

01:01:26.434 --> 01:01:27.695
That's the point.

01:01:28.404 --> 01:01:33.846
He does not commit robbery but gives his food to
the hungry and provides clothing for the naked.

01:01:33.871 --> 01:01:38.699
He withholds his hand from mistreating the poor and takes no
profit from them. He keeps my laws and follows my decrees.

01:01:39.626 --> 01:01:42.958
So we see, this is a holy life
 he strives for, asceticism.

01:01:43.298 --> 01:01:46.588
We must find a healthy balance here.

01:01:46.613 --> 01:01:50.616
Some people blame
everything on their ancestors,

01:01:50.640 --> 01:01:52.747
and I know that person has
no discipline of asceticism,

01:01:52.945 --> 01:01:56.014
doesn't get up, doesn't pray.
And that's a deviation

01:01:56.038 --> 01:01:57.468
we shouldn't look at it that way.

01:01:57.492 --> 01:02:01.930
In my opinion, we should enter this space
only after we have dealt with our weaknesses

01:02:01.954 --> 01:02:05.045
and gained some discipline
in our spiritual life.

01:02:05.125 --> 01:02:09.947
And then it comes into play.
In my experience working with young people

01:02:10.343 --> 01:02:15.028
When you really make an effort,
cast aside your addictions and vices,

01:02:15.052 --> 01:02:16.988
and have a discipline of prayer

01:02:17.107 --> 01:02:20.635
yet in some areas, you still feel
 such oppression and bondage

01:02:21.849 --> 01:02:24.815
then it's most often
connected precisely with this.

01:02:25.109 --> 01:02:27.005
How do I know?

01:02:27.029 --> 01:02:30.948
When we started praying for plenary
indulgences, the Church granted many of them.

01:02:31.154 --> 01:02:33.387
Study the Church's
documents on indulgences.

01:02:34.175 --> 01:02:38.058
Every day you can deliver one
of your ancestors from purgatory.

01:02:38.082 --> 01:02:40.068
Just half an hour of adoration.

01:02:40.425 --> 01:02:42.787
Half an hour of examining
the Holy Scripture.

01:03:08.402 --> 01:03:13.868
Now, my wife would tell me to cut it short.

01:03:15.533 --> 01:03:22.139
Every single day, we can deliver our
ancestors from purgatory, every day.

01:03:22.266 --> 01:03:25.235
Start studying and using that.

01:03:25.535 --> 01:03:28.905
My friend, Rajko Bundalo, talked about

01:03:29.703 --> 01:03:32.992
how God revealed a very
effective model to him.

01:03:33.644 --> 01:03:36.707
Make a table, including father, mother

01:03:37.409 --> 01:03:42.137
grandmothers/fathers, great-grandmothers/fathers,
and great-great-grandmothers/fathers.

01:03:42.428 --> 01:03:45.708
And pray for a plenary indulgence
for each of those souls.

01:03:46.534 --> 01:03:49.742
Pray. What does it
cost you to offer a Mass?

01:03:49.972 --> 01:03:54.068
From the very beginning,
we Catholics pray for our deceased.

01:03:54.552 --> 01:04:00.498
Pay attention to 1 Corinthians 15:29.
They say this is an Old Testament attitude.

01:04:01.148 --> 01:04:06.508
"Now if there is no resurrection, what will
those do who are baptized for the dead?

01:04:06.722 --> 01:04:10.908
If the dead are not raised at all,
why are people baptized for them?"

01:04:10.932 --> 01:04:15.148
In the early Church, it was customary for people to
be baptized on behalf of their deceased relatives

01:04:15.172 --> 01:04:19.228
who did not have the grace to hear
about Christ. Paul praises that attitude.

01:04:19.418 --> 01:04:23.900
We don't have that today, and we can see how
much they held on to it. It's the New Testament.

01:04:24.265 --> 01:04:29.041
Jesus says: "Don't think that I have come to abolish
 the Law or the Prophets; I have come to fulfill them."

01:04:30.406 --> 01:04:32.341
When he argues with the Pharisees

01:04:32.368 --> 01:04:36.311
He says: "So you testify against yourselves that you
are the descendants of those who murdered the prophets.

01:04:36.336 --> 01:04:40.092
Go ahead, then, and complete
 what your ancestors started!"

01:04:40.715 --> 01:04:45.572
Therefore, we see that it's both
a Catholic and a biblical standpoint.

01:04:45.597 --> 01:04:50.668
But don't go to extremes. Your ancestors are
not to blame for everything. You must live holy.

01:04:51.175 --> 01:04:55.974
On the other hand, do not fail to pray
for them; you will receive many graces.

01:04:56.824 --> 01:05:00.948
Because certain sins are
 repeated through families.

01:05:01.059 --> 01:05:03.293
The best example is David.

01:05:03.713 --> 01:05:09.410
While David lived righteously,
his entire family was under protection.

01:05:10.245 --> 01:05:14.828
Then David falls into sin; let's see
the analogy. This is important.

01:05:15.351 --> 01:05:18.239
How did David fall into sin?
Firstly, it was arrogance.

01:05:18.329 --> 01:05:23.148
He didn't go to war, he had fought a lot
 and now he's enjoying his conquests.

01:05:23.865 --> 01:05:27.265
Then he wanders on the terrace;
he needs to pass the time somehow.

01:05:28.795 --> 01:05:36.063
He sees a woman. Fornication: that woman is
 another man's wife, his close friend's woman.

01:05:36.270 --> 01:05:38.097
He sins with her.

01:05:39.404 --> 01:05:42.377
And then he kills her
husband to cover up his sin.

01:05:43.193 --> 01:05:47.107
Do you know what happened
to David's family afterward?

01:05:47.132 --> 01:05:51.446
Just after Solomon was born.
He had an older son, Amnon

01:05:51.505 --> 01:05:55.907
Amnon started feeling a sick
attraction towards his sister

01:05:55.984 --> 01:05:58.788
again fornication, incest,
 a forbidden relationship

01:05:58.843 --> 01:06:03.011
to the point he almost got sick from
it and slept with his sister Tamar.

01:06:03.035 --> 01:06:05.776
Absalom found out and killed him.

01:06:06.889 --> 01:06:10.788
Forbidden relationships,
fornication, murder.

01:06:11.180 --> 01:06:14.732
Why? Because those spirits were released.
Nathan the prophet prophesied it.

01:06:14.906 --> 01:06:19.273
That's why, with our holy life,
 but also with our falls

01:06:19.337 --> 01:06:23.862
we allow either the devil or
blessing to enter our family.

01:06:24.548 --> 01:06:29.268
That's why prayer is very important.
In the spiritual world, it's very fluid.

01:06:29.330 --> 01:06:33.902
I know this might bother someone
because they can't fit it into their puzzle

01:06:34.112 --> 01:06:37.018
What Hebrews 7:9 says

01:06:37.232 --> 01:06:41.348
Levi, who collects
the tenth, paid the tenth through Abraham

01:06:41.569 --> 01:06:44.499
In Abraham, who is Levi's great-grandfather

01:06:44.546 --> 01:06:51.648
because when Melchizedek met Abraham,
Levi was still in the body of his ancestor.

01:06:51.876 --> 01:06:53.696
So, he gives justification.

01:06:53.721 --> 01:06:58.869
How strong the Jews had that
communication that is stereotyped today

01:06:59.098 --> 01:07:02.567
They have the justification
for the tithe to Levi in the fact

01:07:02.592 --> 01:07:06.124
that the great-grandfather
Abraham met Melchizedek.

01:07:06.805 --> 01:07:09.968
That's the Hebrew way of thinking.

01:07:10.092 --> 01:07:14.210
Again, I don't have time to
delve deeper into this

01:07:14.235 --> 01:07:18.533
but maybe take this model
that Rajko Bundalo mentioned,

01:07:18.564 --> 01:07:22.765
the model of presenting
masses, praying rosaries,

01:07:22.789 --> 01:07:24.948
especially if you have
oppression in some area.

01:07:25.231 --> 01:07:27.748
It's like having two rooms

01:07:28.279 --> 01:07:30.713
one room has no one at the door

01:07:30.935 --> 01:07:35.040
while in the other room, 100 people are leaning
against the door, which is immense pressure.

01:07:35.824 --> 01:07:40.723
One had a holy lineage, while the other
had fornicator and alcoholic ancestors

01:07:41.271 --> 01:07:45.023
And what happens? He is still
protected by his baptism, right?

01:07:45.123 --> 01:07:50.219
The doors are closed, but when he
falls, when he unlocks the doors

01:07:51.250 --> 01:07:53.731
This one who had a holy
lineage easily gets out of it.

01:07:53.928 --> 01:07:58.217
While other due to that "fome specati",
those seeds of desire within him

01:07:58.242 --> 01:08:01.868
has a stronger urge towards the same sin,
e.g. alcohol, lust,

01:08:01.892 --> 01:08:04.135
and when he falls, all those come.

01:08:05.546 --> 01:08:07.758
So don't neglect this practice.

01:08:07.900 --> 01:08:13.556
Just let it be in the teachings of the Church,
biblical, and under spiritual guidance.

01:08:13.668 --> 01:08:17.491
Don't do it without a spiritual
leader, someone who can advise you.

01:08:18.526 --> 01:08:21.761
Now we've addressed these three points

01:08:21.785 --> 01:08:26.099
regarding our dealing with
the past and our positioning.

01:08:26.957 --> 01:08:35.086
The fourth point that is controversial and
still causing significant problems today is

01:08:35.420 --> 01:08:37.788
Are there messianic nations today?

01:08:37.812 --> 01:08:42.007
What does it mean when
a nation considers itself chosen?

01:08:43.249 --> 01:08:45.381
There are significant misconceptions.

01:08:45.587 --> 01:08:50.111
If you've been following a bit, the
war between Russia and Ukraine.

01:08:50.472 --> 01:08:56.348
I will explain why this type of delusion
 is much more prevalent in Orthodoxy.

01:08:59.726 --> 01:09:05.107
You have a radical right stream
 of academics in Serbia

01:09:05.490 --> 01:09:08.710
who talk about the cosmic nation,
 about the Serbs heaven

01:09:09.244 --> 01:09:12.926
that's what happens
when you cross the line.

01:09:13.656 --> 01:09:16.938
I'm not saying that our
nation hasn't crossed the line

01:09:16.962 --> 01:09:19.192
and I don't want to wash our hands of that.

01:09:19.224 --> 01:09:22.031
That's why it's important
not to be confused.

01:09:22.211 --> 01:09:26.606
I had a lot of questions about this, because
people hear those prophecies for Croatia.

01:09:26.948 --> 01:09:29.870
We all feel like God is
doing something with us.

01:09:30.195 --> 01:09:32.839
How can we find a healthy middle ground?

01:09:33.066 --> 01:09:36.188
God is the father of all nations;
that's the first truth.

01:09:36.329 --> 01:09:42.621
Pope Francis speaks a lot about it.
I recommend his book Fratelli Tutti.

01:09:42.800 --> 01:09:48.181
Encyclical, Fratelli Tutti, has just come out.
It's analyzing that universal brotherhood.

01:09:49.779 --> 01:09:53.244
We deal a lot with that topic in Bosnia.

01:09:56.425 --> 01:10:01.727
However, God has often chosen
a particular nation in history.

01:10:03.061 --> 01:10:07.988
He chose it for a specific mission
in a very concrete historical context.

01:10:08.248 --> 01:10:13.440
How will you recognize whether it's
about the heresy of a messianic nation

01:10:13.687 --> 01:10:18.548
or God is choosing a nation to
convey a certain truth? By fruits.

01:10:18.897 --> 01:10:24.708
When it's about heresy of a messianic
nation they puts themselves above others

01:10:24.819 --> 01:10:29.755
the fruits are war, killing,
conquest, and significant problems.

01:10:30.350 --> 01:10:36.054
But when God chooses a nation to
bless the rest of the world through it,

01:10:36.094 --> 01:10:39.308
that is then God's choice.

01:10:39.534 --> 01:10:42.820
In a particular historical moment.

01:10:43.326 --> 01:10:50.570
Why are our Orthodox brothers prone
to create these messianic nations?

01:10:51.947 --> 01:10:54.781
I've seen that;
it's a big problem.

01:10:54.883 --> 01:10:59.741
I've traveled to Serbia very often. My
friends are Orthodox priests and theologians

01:10:59.931 --> 01:11:04.545
and one of the main issues is that we don't
understand why they look at us like that.

01:11:05.036 --> 01:11:08.908
To understand Orthodoxy, we must
understand autocephaly.

01:11:08.956 --> 01:11:10.988
I'll explain it briefly.

01:11:11.579 --> 01:11:17.480
When you had the Western and Eastern
Roman Empires, Christianity came in.

01:11:18.098 --> 01:11:22.828
Constantine recognized it, and Theodosius
declared it the official religion in 410.

01:11:23.216 --> 01:11:29.148
At that moment, the Western Roman Empire was
in political decline, and decadence set in.

01:11:29.965 --> 01:11:37.304
The Pope became stronger authority than the
emperor, and the West began to nurture that.

01:11:37.571 --> 01:11:42.956
The Pope was the one who could reconcile
Charlemagne, Louis XIV, and various others.

01:11:43.134 --> 01:11:45.610
That is why democracy was born in the West.

01:11:46.745 --> 01:11:49.990
Because the Pope was the one who
 could stop authorities

01:11:51.331 --> 01:11:55.435
We must not blame our brothers from
the East; that is the historical context.

01:11:55.560 --> 01:11:58.948
At the same time, in the
East, the empire grew

01:11:59.138 --> 01:12:01.410
Constantinople became stronger than Rome.

01:12:02.069 --> 01:12:05.769
The emperor is more
important than the patriarch

01:12:06.023 --> 01:12:09.027
the emperor even dictates
what the patriarch should do.

01:12:09.282 --> 01:12:13.388
They justify it biblically, calling the
political leader 'Basileus,' the anointed one

01:12:13.995 --> 01:12:19.226
and justifying it with David and Solomon,
who were anointed for that service.

01:12:19.845 --> 01:12:24.664
There's no time to go further, but Orthodox
countries continued to develop this way.

01:12:24.815 --> 01:12:27.308
Each country had its own church.

01:12:27.720 --> 01:12:32.682
but here in the West, Stepinac gave his life
so that the Church in Croatia, Yugoslavia

01:12:32.730 --> 01:12:35.404
stay together with the Vatican.

01:12:36.157 --> 01:12:40.193
It's natural that these are
 two opposing worlds.

01:12:40.343 --> 01:12:45.077
I could hold an entire lecture on this,
but I would like you to know this.

01:12:45.371 --> 01:12:48.708
What does it mean if God chooses a nation?

01:12:49.033 --> 01:12:55.110
I have given you very interesting historical
examples, for instance, the Armenians.

01:12:55.953 --> 01:13:00.628
The people who first accepted Christianity
as the official religion in 301.

01:13:00.802 --> 01:13:05.340
Btw, the apostles Bartholomew and
Jude Thaddeus were martyred there,

01:13:05.364 --> 01:13:09.358
and the Armenians have been faithful
to Christ and the Pope from the beginning.

01:13:10.428 --> 01:13:12.940
That nation suffered so much

01:13:13.126 --> 01:13:16.387
it has the largest diaspora, even
larger than Croatia and Ireland.

01:13:20.871 --> 01:13:27.692
"The Happiest People on Earth"
I recommend you to read that book

01:13:27.866 --> 01:13:33.180
When the charismatic renewal came very early
to Armenia, since they were very spiritual,

01:13:33.205 --> 01:13:38.148
and they easily embraced
the baptism in the Spirit

01:13:38.172 --> 01:13:40.901
that came through Russian Pentecostals.

01:13:41.106 --> 01:13:46.587
And then God gave, this is a true
story, a revelation to a prophet.

01:13:47.270 --> 01:13:51.108
He tells him that
great evil will happen

01:13:51.774 --> 01:13:56.659
that they will die, although he was illiterate,
 after hours of prayer and fasting

01:13:56.683 --> 01:14:02.748
that prophecy is kept in a vault in a bank
 because it hasn't been fully fulfilled

01:14:02.914 --> 01:14:08.262
and shows him that they should emigrate
to a country he drew, that is the USA

01:14:08.536 --> 01:14:12.417
and that they will become a great blessing
for that nation and the whole world.

01:14:12.824 --> 01:14:16.988
Of course, as it happens
with prophecies, most declared him insane.

01:14:17.162 --> 01:14:23.268
The people in those communities who
listened to the prophecies fled to California.

01:14:23.514 --> 01:14:30.541
Immediately after that, 1.5 million
Armenians were killed by the Turks

01:14:30.716 --> 01:14:35.866
1,500,000, the biggest
genocide in the 20th century.

01:14:36.080 --> 01:14:40.988
We see how Satan was
furious with that nation precisely

01:14:41.012 --> 01:14:44.500
because of its election
and the mission it had.

01:14:44.826 --> 01:14:49.217
The whole phenomenon of Azusa Street,
the spiritual awakening in USA

01:14:49.384 --> 01:14:52.668
started through Armenian
communities in California.

01:14:52.985 --> 01:14:58.407
Demos Shakarian, the prophet,
was honored by Pope Paul VI

01:14:58.463 --> 01:15:01.534
for his positive influence on
millions of Catholics.

01:15:03.064 --> 01:15:05.663
God chose them for
that purpose.

01:15:06.453 --> 01:15:08.873
Let's talk about Israel.

01:15:09.424 --> 01:15:13.938
We know that according to Church doctrine,
before the judgment day, among other things

01:15:13.962 --> 01:15:18.757
the conversion of the Jews and their
return to the homeland must happen

01:15:19.374 --> 01:15:25.708
In 1947, after 2000 years, the
Israelites returned from over 100 countries

01:15:26.100 --> 01:15:29.145
and re-established the land
God showed Abraham.

01:15:29.514 --> 01:15:31.093
Is that not supernatural?

01:15:32.465 --> 01:15:34.285
Is that possible?

01:15:34.725 --> 01:15:35.708
Well, it's not.

01:15:37.223 --> 01:15:41.675
What happens just before that? In 1947,
 the state of Israel was established.

01:15:41.945 --> 01:15:46.788
Before that, the Holocaust, again genocide,
the devil wanted to eradicate them.

01:15:49.636 --> 01:15:51.468
Let's move on. Portugal

01:15:51.616 --> 01:15:54.751
I have many examples,
 but I won't take long.

01:15:58.107 --> 01:16:01.961
Portugal was given a sign in the 20th
century, the apparitions in Fatima.

01:16:02.226 --> 01:16:07.948
Amidst World War I, the Virgin
Mary appears to three illiterate children

01:16:08.892 --> 01:16:15.348
and tells them that if the world
does not convert, an even worse war will occur

01:16:15.569 --> 01:16:19.267
The Red Dragon from Russia,
communism, will engulf Europe

01:16:19.349 --> 01:16:24.247
priests and believers will suffer, and the
bishop in white, will fall from a bullet.

01:16:24.961 --> 01:16:31.628
All three things happened, although this
was spoken in 1917., except in Portugal.

01:16:31.842 --> 01:16:37.388
God showed how much power there
is if we listen to what Our Lady tells us.

01:16:37.506 --> 01:16:40.437
Our Lady asked for the
consecration to her heart.

01:16:40.462 --> 01:16:46.188
On the Feast days of Our Lady of Fatima,
May 13 in 1931 and 1936, the bishops,

01:16:46.580 --> 01:16:53.144
at the prompting of Lucia from Fatima, consecrated
Portugal to the Immaculate Heart of Mary.

01:16:53.602 --> 01:16:59.788
February 6, 1939, Lucia wrote
to the Bishop of Lisbon, Da Silva

01:16:59.812 --> 01:17:04.707
exactly six months before
the start of World War II.

01:17:05.175 --> 01:17:09.908
Portugal will be spared from the war that
will soon be initiated by Hitler's Germany

01:17:09.932 --> 01:17:12.556
solely because of the consecration
to the Immaculate Heart of Mary.

01:17:12.628 --> 01:17:16.313
The letter is preserved, archived,
 precisely six months before.

01:17:17.059 --> 01:17:20.508
What if we listen to
what God is telling us?

01:17:20.887 --> 01:17:23.878
That's why we speak about it here today.

01:17:24.060 --> 01:17:28.659
Because the choosing of Portugal
continued with the Church in Croatia

01:17:29.342 --> 01:17:35.251
Our Lady in Medjugorje said on August 25,
1991, to the visionary Marija Pavlovic Lunetti:

01:17:35.623 --> 01:17:41.335
What I began in Fatima, I will finish
in Medjugorje; my heart will triumph.

01:17:41.732 --> 01:17:45.268
We are chosen that through us

01:17:45.327 --> 01:17:49.427
the light may come to Europe,
not to elevate ourselves above others.

01:17:52.061 --> 01:17:55.551
The message of Medjugorje
has encircled the whole world.

01:17:55.576 --> 01:17:58.388
Go to Youth Festival,
experience all that rised flags.

01:18:00.728 --> 01:18:03.561
And we behave nonchalantly about it.

01:18:03.688 --> 01:18:09.579
I will show you how much disobedience
to God's promptings has cost us.

01:18:09.705 --> 01:18:10.842
How costly!

01:18:11.008 --> 01:18:15.964
Our Lady appeared in Medjugorje in
1981, saying, I am the Queen of Peace.

01:18:16.178 --> 01:18:20.588
A year later, in 1982, she appeared
in Kibeho, Rwanda

01:18:21.659 --> 01:18:24.786
and asked for a prayer for peace.
You know how they mocked

01:18:25.420 --> 01:18:31.731
Yugoslavia was then, brotherhood and unity,
united nations, what a war, what a queen of peace.

01:18:32.683 --> 01:18:39.291
Ten years after the bloodiest war in Europe since
World War II broke out in Bosnia and Herzegovina

01:18:39.315 --> 01:18:42.563
100 thousand people lost their lives.

01:18:44.195 --> 01:18:49.068
In 1994, in Africa, precisely in Rwanda

01:18:49.675 --> 01:18:53.419
the biggest genocide since
 World War II occurred

01:18:53.577 --> 01:19:03.737
a 1.5 million people died in
the conflict between two tribes in Rwanda.

01:19:06.062 --> 01:19:11.220
The only two genocides after World War
II are Bosnia and Herzegovina and Rwanda.

01:19:11.577 --> 01:19:13.444
Has the Lady given enough time?

01:19:13.752 --> 01:19:15.388
Well, yes, ten years.

01:19:15.617 --> 01:19:17.675
Did people listen?
They didn't.

01:19:17.786 --> 01:19:22.269
What is comforting is that
the message of Medjugorje has not ended.

01:19:23.393 --> 01:19:25.788
The apparitions continued.

01:19:26.579 --> 01:19:29.934
But we won't just stay
with the apparitions.

01:19:29.974 --> 01:19:34.706
I would like that you see that divine
choosing God gave to our nation.

01:19:35.462 --> 01:19:37.327
You are responsible for the same.

01:19:40.383 --> 01:19:43.068
Confirmations came from various sides.

01:19:43.631 --> 01:19:49.428
I will specifically highlight the message
that Our Lady gave to Don Stefano Gobbi.

01:19:49.618 --> 01:19:54.987
a priest who has had locutions, inner speeches
 from the Blessed Virgin Mary, his whole life.

01:19:56.472 --> 01:20:01.068
He came to Croatia in 1996,
right after the war

01:20:01.552 --> 01:20:06.348
and in the presence of Cardinal Franjo
Kuharić, he received a locution from Our Lady.

01:20:06.776 --> 01:20:10.462
There was a praying gathering
at Jordanovac with the people.

01:20:10.700 --> 01:20:15.797
Pay attention to what Our Lady says about
our nation and the war we went through:

01:20:16.090 --> 01:20:21.408
How pleased I'm with the cenacle you had here
with the priests and faithful of my movement

01:20:21.615 --> 01:20:25.452
presided over by the cardinal,
the archbishop I greatly love and protect.

01:20:26.165 --> 01:20:30.816
We see the choosing
of a nation and a people

01:20:31.062 --> 01:20:37.513
"Upon this nation my enemy became furious,
bringing into it a severe trial of violence and war.

01:20:38.369 --> 01:20:41.475
How much suffering
my children had to endure

01:20:41.499 --> 01:20:45.468
I interceded to give them
the great gift of liberation and peace."

01:20:45.911 --> 01:20:50.319
Do you remember all those rosaries
that were prayed and worn around the neck?

01:20:50.530 --> 01:20:53.948
I interceded to give them the
great gift of liberation and peace

01:20:54.051 --> 01:20:54.773
but

01:20:55.686 --> 01:20:59.348
this is the harder part now;
"now, even greater torments await you."

01:21:00.196 --> 01:21:02.665
That's what's happening to us now.

01:21:02.788 --> 01:21:07.642
Because the spiritual persecution what
is happening to us will be much harder

01:21:07.853 --> 01:21:10.903
because it is more insidious
and drags souls away more easily.

01:21:10.988 --> 01:21:14.925
"From now on, even greater torments
are expected, but do not fear, little flock

01:21:14.964 --> 01:21:18.940
it pleased the Heavenly Father to give
you the kingdom of my Immaculate Heart."

01:21:19.287 --> 01:21:20.900
Fear not, little flock

01:21:21.058 --> 01:21:25.329
Your heavenly mother has granted you
the gift to gather from all sides

01:21:25.397 --> 01:21:27.257
into her victorious army

01:21:27.328 --> 01:21:32.443
Here, we see indications of this return,
with which I will conclude.

01:21:33.013 --> 01:21:34.060
She continues.

01:21:35.239 --> 01:21:37.298
The hour of decisive battle has come.

01:21:37.389 --> 01:21:42.005
Satan has already reached the peak of
his power, and now, even within the Church,

01:21:42.038 --> 01:21:47.319
he will complete his work as much as the Lord
allowed him for its most painful cleansing."

01:21:48.086 --> 01:21:52.628
And that's what we see in the churches now
in the West, those altars in rainbow colors

01:21:53.041 --> 01:21:56.102
that's that painful cleansing,
Satan in the Church.

01:21:56.480 --> 01:22:01.775
"Moments you will live through are important
because all the events I prophesied will come true.

01:22:02.117 --> 01:22:07.468
The time you will perfectly glorify Jesus has come.
You are the consolation of His abandonment.

01:22:07.586 --> 01:22:10.434
You are the profound
joy of His divine heart.

01:22:10.584 --> 01:22:16.212
Do not fear, little flock, be my little children
whom I have gathered around of the world

01:22:16.306 --> 01:22:20.675
for the great battle between God and Satan,
between the forces of good and evil."

01:22:20.858 --> 01:22:26.788
During the homeland war, St John Paul II
said it was a cosmic conflict between good and evil.

01:22:28.367 --> 01:22:32.788
Furthermore, pay attention;
this sentence must fill you with awe.

01:22:33.335 --> 01:22:38.468
"The Lord will triumph through me" and it is not
difficult for us to accept; we are a Marian people

01:22:39.094 --> 01:22:44.628
"Through me, His little maid, but I, I will
triumph through you, my little children."

01:22:45.017 --> 01:22:46.493
And that is your responsibility.

01:22:46.707 --> 01:22:52.666
Your responsibility for a holy life,
for prayer, for listening to the Spirit.

01:22:53.586 --> 01:22:57.748
"What happened in this nation,
becomes a sign for everyone.

01:22:58.111 --> 01:23:02.675
Because of your faithfulness to Jesus, to your
heavenly Mother, to the Church, and to the Pope

01:23:02.894 --> 01:23:06.366
Satan has attacked her in
an attempt to destroy her.

01:23:06.728 --> 01:23:12.627
With this goal in mind, all satanic
and Masonic forces joined together.

01:23:12.944 --> 01:23:17.217
However, I myself marked
the moment of their defeat."

01:23:18.010 --> 01:23:19.188
And that is comforting

01:23:21.672 --> 01:23:24.388
It will happen. They have joined forces.

01:23:24.642 --> 01:23:29.988
Specifically, when we talk about Medjugorje,
about the Church in Bosnia and Herzegovina.

01:23:30.345 --> 01:23:33.268
We use the term the Church of the Croats.

01:23:36.204 --> 01:23:41.068
Of all the amendments made at Dayton,
up to this ninth and final loose Schmidt's

01:23:41.318 --> 01:23:43.708
all were against Croatian Catholics.

01:23:44.716 --> 01:23:50.188
Can you believe this,
at the beginning of the 21st century

01:23:50.561 --> 01:23:55.388
tanks of the international community
invasioned the Herzegovina Bank in Mostar

01:23:55.618 --> 01:24:01.983
robbed that bank without any evidence, damaged
several thousands of depositors and companies

01:24:02.015 --> 01:24:04.868
it was the backbone of the
Croats in Bosnia and Herzegovina.

01:24:05.185 --> 01:24:09.789
They have not returned it to this day.
 Tanks robbed the bank,

01:24:09.814 --> 01:24:15.712
 trampled and spat on  the pictures
of Saint John Paul II that were there.

01:24:16.445 --> 01:24:19.908
How will you explain and justify that?

01:24:20.043 --> 01:24:25.123
But like with this sentence:
"all satanic and Masonic joined forces."

01:24:27.202 --> 01:24:30.493
There are countless examples,
but we don't have time

01:24:30.787 --> 01:24:36.708
I could tell you how many things have
happened just in Bosnia and Herzegovina.

01:24:37.906 --> 01:24:42.092
People from other
denominations have also discussed this.

01:24:42.250 --> 01:24:45.868
Pope Francis encourages
us to use good and healthy discernment

01:24:45.959 --> 01:24:49.475
to listen what the Spirit is doing among
our Protestant and Orthodox brothers.

01:24:50.000 --> 01:24:55.614
If we know our doctrine and faith
well, we can certainly learn from them.

01:24:56.032 --> 01:25:00.140
Even though we have the fullness
of truth, many of us have neglected it

01:25:00.450 --> 01:25:06.505
but we know that some of their communities
fervently fast, pray, listen, and seek God's word.

01:25:06.639 --> 01:25:08.106
Do not be exclusive.

01:25:08.480 --> 01:25:10.660
The Pope encourages, learn from them

01:25:11.041 --> 01:25:13.668
through discernment retain what is good.

01:25:14.643 --> 01:25:19.297
An American well-known
Protestant evangelist, Patricia King

01:25:19.487 --> 01:25:23.356
spoke about the new prophetic
waves and conversions that are coming.

01:25:23.435 --> 01:25:26.755
During the broadcast, even though
she has no idea about Croatia

01:25:27.477 --> 01:25:31.885
She says:
"The word Croatia, comes to me."

01:25:33.495 --> 01:25:38.707
"I feel that God is blessing
that country in a special way"

01:25:38.946 --> 01:25:43.068
"He is breathing the Holy Spirit into it,
on everyone who is connected with it. "

01:25:44.798 --> 01:25:47.180
And that this country will
become a light to Europe.

01:26:26.240 --> 01:26:31.800
John Mulinde, a well-known
Ugandan Pentecostal pastor

01:26:32.264 --> 01:26:38.059
Uganda strongly live ecumenism. There
is indeed brotherhood among denominations.

01:26:38.511 --> 01:26:42.948
A man who had never heard of
Croatia, spends time in prayer and fasting

01:26:42.972 --> 01:26:46.000
and God shows him Europe in dense darkness

01:26:46.548 --> 01:26:50.085
and how light breaks through from
only one place, from Croatia.

01:26:50.109 --> 01:26:56.521
He goes to Croatia and holds seminars, and
many Catholic priests have received him.

01:26:57.003 --> 01:27:03.188
I feel that we need to invest in Croatia.
I have never been to Croatia.

01:27:05.060 --> 01:27:07.548
Croatia has been calling
me for several years.

01:27:08.389 --> 01:27:12.468
I met some Croats in Israel,
different people every year

01:27:16.300 --> 01:27:20.988
and they all say:
"please come, help us."

01:27:23.202 --> 01:27:25.868
People who have no
connections confirm this.

01:27:28.034 --> 01:27:29.304
And because of that

01:27:30.204 --> 01:27:34.689
we must be aware that each of us has a
responsibility in this spiritual awakening.

01:27:35.525 --> 01:27:41.117
You also saw that
magnificent event on Maksimir

01:27:42.181 --> 01:27:44.047
Who could gather
that if not the Holy Spirit?

01:27:44.231 --> 01:27:49.073
When some newspapers, which are against us,
went to investigate who was behind this

01:27:49.127 --> 01:27:55.651
is it the Kaptol?
but they see it's not the Kaptol

01:27:55.818 --> 01:28:00.188
is it politics?
but they see no one is behind it.

01:28:00.512 --> 01:28:05.659
When they had to admit that the Holy Spirit
gathered them; they stopped writing about it.

01:28:05.873 --> 01:28:11.179
Fifty thousand people, so many
young, come to glorify God and pay for it.

01:28:11.767 --> 01:28:17.235
Orban tried to do the same thing, even paid people
to come, but the stadium was still half empty.

01:28:17.813 --> 01:28:19.451
Some of ours were there.

01:28:23.072 --> 01:28:26.619
Why? Something is happening.
Find your place in it

01:28:26.928 --> 01:28:29.668
That is very, very important.

01:28:34.040 --> 01:28:36.319
God did not give it to us for ourselves

01:28:36.513 --> 01:28:41.228
it must first become a blessing for
Europe and then a blessing for the world.

01:28:41.727 --> 01:28:45.847
Now we come to the
last part, the tricky one

01:28:46.203 --> 01:28:51.080
it's often said that we should not talk
about it, that it deepens the wounds.

01:28:51.346 --> 01:28:55.692
I will speak in the name of God
 based on what the Lord has shown me

01:28:55.819 --> 01:29:02.348
You take what you like, what you feel
is yours, and what is not, do not take.

01:29:02.528 --> 01:29:08.922
I have prepared a 5-minute video
to wake you up a little, be careful.

01:29:09.105 --> 01:29:13.268
This is the position of Europe in 2007.

01:29:13.410 --> 01:29:15.690
It is very interesting;
there are many animations.

01:29:15.825 --> 01:29:21.628
It will wake you up a little more, and
then we will conclude with the fifth point.

01:29:22.723 --> 01:29:26.504
To give you insight into what
is happening around us.

01:34:14.594 --> 01:34:19.921
Are you shocked,
or did you somehow anticipate this?

01:34:20.848 --> 01:34:23.668
Those who have lived abroad know.

01:34:28.643 --> 01:34:33.094
Please do not think that I have something
against Muslims; it's not a problem at all.

01:34:33.127 --> 01:34:38.868
In Bosnia, we have dialogues for peace;
the problem is that we are disappearing.

01:34:39.971 --> 01:34:45.843
We, as Christians, cannot be indifferent
if we genuinely believe in our values.

01:34:46.398 --> 01:34:49.708
I leave it to your intelligence to assess.

01:34:49.771 --> 01:34:55.428
This was in 2007, before the Arab
Spring, and the migrant crisis in 2015.

01:34:55.665 --> 01:35:02.548
Calculated with the previous immigration rate.
Try to imagine the situation today.

01:35:05.143 --> 01:35:12.188
That means the world we are going
to leave to our grandchildren

01:35:12.536 --> 01:35:16.183
even to our children,
may not look the same.

01:35:18.313 --> 01:35:22.237
West, as we can see,
it is no longer possible to restore

01:35:22.333 --> 01:35:26.219
and unfortunately, there is not
even that healthy core in the faith.

01:35:26.782 --> 01:35:31.810
In some places, there are not even ten
righteous people from Sodom who would save it.

01:35:32.730 --> 01:35:37.012
However, it is not all lost here yet

01:35:37.373 --> 01:35:43.083
and what will be crucial will
involve the return of the diaspora.

01:35:43.654 --> 01:35:49.388
That is how our nation can be saved,
I appeal to everyone to think about it.

01:35:50.761 --> 01:35:56.308
How many of us live in
the diaspora, and how is life lived?

01:35:56.616 --> 01:36:01.811
As patriots, we have seen the biblical basis
for that, and as those who cherish memory

01:36:01.835 --> 01:36:06.108
who are connected with their homeland
and recognize what God is doing here.

01:36:06.480 --> 01:36:09.295
I appeal to your conscience, think.

01:36:11.380 --> 01:36:13.128
Think about it, pray.

01:36:13.267 --> 01:36:18.214
I know many are drawn in their hearts,
but the mind does not allow it.

01:36:18.593 --> 01:36:21.861
But now, even the mind shows,
so what are the costs of heating

01:36:21.885 --> 01:36:25.108
what kind of hunger is this,
and what insecurity is this?

01:36:26.592 --> 01:36:32.548
What ideology has penetrated
every pore of education?

01:36:33.199 --> 01:36:35.157
Do I want that for my children?

01:36:35.772 --> 01:36:37.603
The biggest lie I've heard

01:36:38.166 --> 01:36:41.468
Or rather the two biggest lies
 I hear when people leave

01:36:41.745 --> 01:36:43.396
"I'm going for my children."

01:36:43.856 --> 01:36:44.587
Why?

01:36:45.213 --> 01:36:50.308
So they can indoctrinate your children with
monstrous ideologies from the earliest age?

01:36:51.950 --> 01:36:54.382
And the second:
"I'm going to be a light there."

01:36:56.484 --> 01:36:59.708
And they returns as ruins.
Many such examples I have had.

01:37:00.564 --> 01:37:04.708
We must listen to who is leading us
 and who is forcing us to go.

01:37:05.072 --> 01:37:09.068
If it's God, if it's evangelistic,
great, thank God, be a light there.

01:37:09.195 --> 01:37:11.348
There are such examples.

01:37:11.546 --> 01:37:15.037
I'm not saying there aren't any,
but the vast majority are not like that.

01:37:15.295 --> 01:37:19.908
In the Old Testament, exile never,
 absolutely never happened

01:37:20.034 --> 01:37:23.681
without being the result
of disobedience and curse.

01:37:24.452 --> 01:37:28.100
In the New Testament, we have the
example of exile so that faith may spread

01:37:28.329 --> 01:37:33.660
Again, we must find a middle ground
between these two extremes.

01:37:34.096 --> 01:37:39.228
We should not talk that it's definitely a curse
and burden on the people who have gone there.

01:37:41.909 --> 01:37:45.827
But also not say that we all
 went there to be light

01:37:45.927 --> 01:37:48.857
because we see that
there is not so much light.

01:37:49.399 --> 01:37:51.531
So, it's a question
of how brightly we shine.

01:37:52.397 --> 01:37:54.668
I put it on your heart to reflect on this.

01:37:59.831 --> 01:38:04.000
Countless examples show that
whenever the Israelites fled in exile

01:38:04.148 --> 01:38:06.088
it was due to disobedience and curse

01:38:06.172 --> 01:38:09.140
except in Jeremiah 29:4-14.

01:38:09.480 --> 01:38:13.028
When they went to Babylon
because of disobedience

01:38:13.734 --> 01:38:16.748
but Jeremiah advised them to stay there

01:38:16.945 --> 01:38:19.576
and those are the two texts
 that God showed me.

01:38:19.619 --> 01:38:21.908
I will convey what came to me in prayer

01:38:22.049 --> 01:38:24.950
I encourage all who listen
to us from the diaspora to

01:38:24.974 --> 01:38:29.554
enter their room and pray to see
what God is telling them.

01:38:30.372 --> 01:38:32.550
The first text is Jeremiah 29:4-14.

01:38:38.501 --> 01:38:43.120
The Israelites are in exile in Babylon,
and he writes them a circular letter.

01:38:43.378 --> 01:38:49.195
This is the only time in the Old Testament
where he says: Stay, but for a while.

01:38:49.876 --> 01:38:52.787
"This is what the Lord Almighty

01:38:52.817 --> 01:38:56.188
says to all those I carried
into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon

01:38:56.656 --> 01:39:01.148
“Build houses and settle down;
plant gardens and eat what they produce.

01:39:01.354 --> 01:39:03.628
Marry and have sons and daughters;

01:39:03.826 --> 01:39:08.767
Marry your sons and daughters,
so that they too may have sons and daughters.

01:39:08.958 --> 01:39:11.108
Increase in number there;
do not decrease.

01:39:11.925 --> 01:39:16.148
Seek the peace of the city
to which I have carried you into exile.

01:39:16.667 --> 01:39:19.625
Pray for it, because if it prospers,
you too will prosper.”

01:39:20.104 --> 01:39:22.339
This is what the Lord says:

01:39:22.454 --> 01:39:26.062
"When seventy years
are completed for Babylon

01:39:26.172 --> 01:39:30.696
I will come to you and fulfill my good
promise to bring you back to this place.

01:39:31.048 --> 01:39:33.560
For I know the plans I have for you.

01:39:33.687 --> 01:39:38.034
Plans to prosper you and not to harm you,
plans to give you hope and a future."

01:39:38.288 --> 01:39:39.503
What is this all about?

01:39:40.201 --> 01:39:43.363
That is the text that the
Lord put on my heart for this time.

01:39:43.419 --> 01:39:47.908
Jeremiah tells them to stay,
and that's what happened to our people.

01:39:47.995 --> 01:39:52.358
Be fruitful and become
many, prosper, learn

01:39:52.839 --> 01:39:56.068
but then he says
until the seventieth year.

01:39:56.369 --> 01:39:57.076
Why?

01:39:57.406 --> 01:40:00.868
Because at that moment,
Babylon crossed the red line.

01:40:01.510 --> 01:40:04.620
Babylon was destroyed,
the Persian kingdom destroyed it.

01:40:07.405 --> 01:40:11.190
What I feel and personally deeply believe,
 and you may or may not agree

01:40:11.360 --> 01:40:16.708
is that many countries where
our people live have crossed the red line.

01:40:16.993 --> 01:40:21.148
Listen to the excellent lecture by the
American exorcist Chad Ripperger

01:40:21.345 --> 01:40:25.073
about how when specific
laws are passed that are against God,

01:40:25.129 --> 01:40:30.755
literally, that country is handed over
to particular demons who destroy it.

01:40:32.255 --> 01:40:33.803
Our people live there.

01:40:34.564 --> 01:40:36.805
Remember that Lot fled from Sodom.

01:40:36.944 --> 01:40:39.505
There is a red line
after which God cuts off.

01:40:40.377 --> 01:40:43.260
This isn't conspiracy theory.
Look at history.

01:40:43.296 --> 01:40:46.665
Has any civilization
that became decadent survived?

01:40:47.098 --> 01:40:48.291
They all collapsed

01:40:48.906 --> 01:40:53.388
That is why the other text
that the Lord has put on my heart

01:40:53.412 --> 01:40:55.733
which I put on your heart to pray

01:40:58.577 --> 01:41:00.283
Revelation 18:1-8.

01:41:00.975 --> 01:41:06.708
It is a comparison with places where many
of our people, unfortunately, live today.

01:41:07.763 --> 01:41:11.695
"After this I saw another angel coming
down from heaven. He had great authority

01:41:11.720 --> 01:41:15.788
and the earth was illuminated by his
splendor. With a mighty voice he shouted:

01:41:15.874 --> 01:41:20.408
“ Fallen! Fallen is Babylon the Great!
She has become a dwelling for demons

01:41:20.448 --> 01:41:24.868
and a haunt for every impure spirit, a
haunt for every unclean bird and animal.

01:41:24.893 --> 01:41:28.157
For all the nations have drunk
the maddening wine of her adulteries.

01:41:28.395 --> 01:41:31.206
The kings of the earth
committed adultery with her

01:41:31.230 --> 01:41:34.348
and the merchants grew
rich from her excessive luxuries.”

01:41:34.657 --> 01:41:36.358
I don't need to describe it further.

01:41:36.528 --> 01:41:39.953
Due to the moral decline,
it becomes a dwelling place of demons

01:41:40.095 --> 01:41:43.283
but there is strong economic growth

01:41:43.314 --> 01:41:48.057
so all merchants and kings are drunk
by her fornication and her immense luxury.

01:41:48.655 --> 01:41:52.908
since the Israelite people are there

01:41:53.281 --> 01:41:55.006
the voice of God goes to that people

01:41:55.266 --> 01:41:59.603
"Then I heard another voice from heaven:
"Come out of her, my people

01:41:59.767 --> 01:42:05.542
so that you will not share in her sins, so
that you will not receive any of her plagues

01:42:05.915 --> 01:42:10.500
for her sins are piled up to heaven,
and God has remembered her crimes.

01:42:10.825 --> 01:42:14.551
Give back to her as she has given;
pay her back double for what she has done.

01:42:16.820 --> 01:42:20.889
This is God's cry, "come out"

01:42:21.523 --> 01:42:26.188
Why? By living in such an
atmosphere, we become participants.

01:42:26.362 --> 01:42:29.308
Why did Lot and his family
have to leave Sodom?

01:42:29.442 --> 01:42:33.483
Because at one point, you can't be in
Chernobyl for so long without being radiated.

01:42:34.673 --> 01:42:35.873
Do you understand?

01:42:37.015 --> 01:42:40.126
Examine whether the line has been crossed.

01:42:40.737 --> 01:42:43.628
Is this what you really
want for your children?

01:42:46.024 --> 01:42:48.108
You have somewhere to go.

01:42:51.084 --> 01:42:55.964
Where God calls you and
where your roots are.

01:42:59.917 --> 01:43:02.766
Return there if you want to be strong.

01:43:02.986 --> 01:43:04.828
We started with eradication.

01:43:05.066 --> 01:43:10.076
Let's now consider one strong tree.
Parable from the Gospel.

01:43:10.464 --> 01:43:12.443
What kind of strong tree is that?

01:43:12.995 --> 01:43:14.268
It is rooted.

01:43:14.974 --> 01:43:16.628
Do you know what it feeds on?

01:43:17.342 --> 01:43:22.082
I am an agronomist, so let me
discuss this with you a little.

01:43:22.106 --> 01:43:24.308
It feeds on humus.

01:43:24.712 --> 01:43:26.622
Do you know how humus is formed?

01:43:26.838 --> 01:43:31.881
Humus is formed through thousands
and thousands of years of organisms dying

01:43:31.905 --> 01:43:37.507
and creating organic soil with their
death, which today that tree can eat from.

01:43:38.801 --> 01:43:41.876
Also your faith was born
through the suffering and death

01:43:41.900 --> 01:43:45.548
of thousands of generations
that we often forget.

01:43:46.149 --> 01:43:47.449
Then that tree

01:43:47.935 --> 01:43:52.388
nourished in that way,
 can grow towards the sky

01:43:53.534 --> 01:43:56.288
and feed on the sun through photosynthesis.

01:43:57.356 --> 01:44:00.884
That's how we are also called
by God to receive new incentives

01:44:00.908 --> 01:44:04.948
with awareness of our roots and
listening to what God wants to give us.

01:44:05.559 --> 01:44:10.908
We must become such trees
to fulfill what God requires of our people.

01:44:13.026 --> 01:44:18.268
Because as much as the
Israelites enjoyed themselves in Babylon

01:44:18.656 --> 01:44:21.031
prospered and became many

01:44:22.261 --> 01:44:26.374
and if they were so happy,
they wouldn't have sung Psalm 137

01:44:26.493 --> 01:44:32.588
"By the rivers of Babylon we sat
and wept when we remembered Zion."

01:44:32.945 --> 01:44:33.985
Their homeland.

01:44:34.325 --> 01:44:38.428
"If I forget you, Jerusalem,
may my right hand forget its skill.

01:44:38.690 --> 01:44:43.348
May my tongue cling to the roof of
my mouth if I do not remember you,

01:44:44.050 --> 01:44:48.028
if I do not consider
Jerusalem my highest joy."

01:44:48.417 --> 01:44:53.908
That's what they sang. And so many
of our people inside mourn and die.

01:44:56.121 --> 01:44:58.504
As our writer Ivo Andrić said:

01:44:58.709 --> 01:45:00.814
"Here I became,
here I will disappear

01:45:01.116 --> 01:45:05.675
here I watched the heavenly infinite
and the open sea on which the eye rests.

01:45:06.612 --> 01:45:11.268
I wouldn't trade this for any place in the world;
there may be more beautiful ones, but not dearer.

01:45:11.822 --> 01:45:14.802
This place, this is me,
this is my life, my love

01:45:14.933 --> 01:45:19.548
this is my cradle, my grave,
my beginning, and my end."

01:45:21.961 --> 01:45:26.908
I'm not saying quick
decisions should be made tomorrow

01:45:27.662 --> 01:45:31.048
but to become aware,
I first address the diaspora.

01:45:31.116 --> 01:45:34.708
Your homeland needs you,
it's not too late here

01:45:36.541 --> 01:45:40.562
and you enter into the nation
 God looks at in a particular way.

01:45:40.803 --> 01:45:47.539
If you fear what you will eat
and whether you will have enough

01:45:48.483 --> 01:45:51.629
I'll tell you a true story

01:45:52.930 --> 01:45:57.308
written by Martin Đurđević
in his memoirs from the Balkans.

01:45:57.689 --> 01:46:00.573
When the uprising broke out in Herzegovina

01:46:00.656 --> 01:46:03.812
against the Turkish authorities
during the Turkish-Austro-Hungarian war

01:46:04.153 --> 01:46:08.263
the people of Herzegovina finally felt
that they would throw off that yoke

01:46:08.536 --> 01:46:12.988
Then foreign diplomats came to
 negotiate, the British,

01:46:13.428 --> 01:46:18.380
you can guess whose side they were
on, on the Turkish, of course, as today.

01:46:19.990 --> 01:46:22.788
They are now going to persuade
the insurgents to give up.

01:46:24.057 --> 01:46:27.828
This is a true event;
Martin Đurđević conveys that dialogue.

01:46:28.264 --> 01:46:32.508
They say: your uprising and actions
are not justified, said the consuls.

01:46:33.270 --> 01:46:37.939
Long-suffering justifies our uprising-
the leaders of the rebellion replied.

01:46:38.581 --> 01:46:43.502
But the Sultan has the power and the army
to crush you all, the consuls welcomed.

01:46:45.612 --> 01:46:50.412
They have crushed us and tortured us
for 500 years, so here we are still alive

01:46:51.355 --> 01:46:57.333
to shed our last drop of blood
for freedom, justified the leaders.

01:46:58.261 --> 01:47:03.880
And when you eat up that little bread you
have in your bag, what will you eat then?

01:47:03.905 --> 01:47:06.108
Threatened the consuls with sanctions.

01:47:07.218 --> 01:47:10.948
Mijo Ljuban from Sjekose grabbed
a handful of earth in front of him

01:47:11.393 --> 01:47:12.839
put the earth in his mouth

01:47:13.263 --> 01:47:16.988
chewed it, and swallowed it
in front of everyone and said:

01:47:17.829 --> 01:47:22.948
Here, this is God's food;
it will never run out for us.

01:47:24.320 --> 01:47:29.778
They say that English consul Holmes
 cried when he saw that sight.

01:47:31.174 --> 01:47:31.814
Amen.

01:47:55.330 --> 01:47:59.819
Thanks and praise be to God for
everything, I did not speak in my own name

01:48:00.454 --> 01:48:04.655
but also in the name of God, I believe,
and in the name of your ancestors

01:48:04.696 --> 01:48:11.117
whom I met while driving around Bosnia and
Croatia, through massacre sites, through pits

01:48:11.379 --> 01:48:15.788
and felt in my spirit and my heart,
their suffering and pain

01:48:15.812 --> 01:48:21.540
and desire and longing for what we are
now living, and which we sell so cheaply.

01:48:22.111 --> 01:48:23.839
I do this mostly for them.

01:48:24.470 --> 01:48:28.606
God has given me a special love,
a pastoral that is not so common.

01:48:28.825 --> 01:48:34.748
There is no larger killing field, encampment
we have not visited, prayed or had holy masses at.

01:48:35.262 --> 01:48:40.452
Believe me, what we live in today is paid
dearly and sold cheaply. Don't let that happen.

